00:01:20.470 --> 00:01:23.040 align:middle line:84%
So without further ado,
let's go into the life

00:01:23.040 --> 00:01:24.300 align:middle line:90%
and times of John Dee.

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:26.860 align:middle line:84%
Give us a context
for his life, OK.

00:01:26.860 --> 00:01:27.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Sure.

00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:29.730 align:middle line:10%
So the reason this
person is so important

00:01:29.730 --> 00:01:33.370 align:middle line:10%
is because in our culture, at
a certain point in our history,

00:01:33.370 --> 00:01:34.940 align:middle line:10%
science and magic diverged.

00:01:34.940 --> 00:01:36.510 align:middle line:90%
They used to be the same thing.

00:01:36.510 --> 00:01:38.070 align:middle line:84%
People who were
interested in science

00:01:38.070 --> 00:01:40.750 align:middle line:84%
were also interested in the
esoteric side of things.

00:01:40.750 --> 00:01:42.870 align:middle line:84%
And then they split and
they went their own ways.

00:01:42.870 --> 00:01:45.690 align:middle line:84%
And science became modern
science and magic kind of

00:01:45.690 --> 00:01:49.740 align:middle line:90%
went off into its own world.

00:01:49.740 --> 00:01:52.320 align:middle line:84%
But John Dee, who was
the scientific advisor

00:01:52.320 --> 00:01:55.530 align:middle line:84%
to Queen Elizabeth I and one
of the most brilliant people

00:01:55.530 --> 00:01:57.280 align:middle line:84%
of the 16th century,
the person who

00:01:57.280 --> 00:02:00.000 align:middle line:84%
was responsible for bringing
mathematics to the public,

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.880 align:middle line:84%
for coming up with the
phrase, the "British Empire,"

00:02:02.880 --> 00:02:04.510 align:middle line:84%
and laying down
the plans for there

00:02:04.510 --> 00:02:06.960 align:middle line:84%
to be a British
empire, who really laid

00:02:06.960 --> 00:02:09.690 align:middle line:84%
the groundwork for
modern science to happen,

00:02:09.690 --> 00:02:12.660 align:middle line:84%
was also completely
fascinated with magic

00:02:12.660 --> 00:02:13.890 align:middle line:90%
and the esoteric world.

00:02:13.890 --> 00:02:15.930 align:middle line:84%
And is maybe one of the
most brilliant thinkers

00:02:15.930 --> 00:02:18.620 align:middle line:90%
that spirituality has produced.

00:02:18.620 --> 00:02:22.530 align:middle line:84%
And is one of the rare people
who synthesized the two.

00:02:22.530 --> 00:02:24.089 align:middle line:84%
And I say synthesized,
but really

00:02:24.089 --> 00:02:25.380 align:middle line:90%
they just hadn't separated yet.

00:02:25.380 --> 00:02:27.010 align:middle line:90%
And they were the same thing.

00:02:27.010 --> 00:02:29.726 align:middle line:84%
So in our modern world,
we're coming to a point

00:02:29.726 --> 00:02:31.350 align:middle line:84%
now as a culture
where these things are

00:02:31.350 --> 00:02:32.760 align:middle line:90%
starting to come back together.

00:02:32.760 --> 00:02:34.200 align:middle line:84%
And people are
interested in both,

00:02:34.200 --> 00:02:37.620 align:middle line:84%
are interested in science,
wonderfully so, and also

00:02:37.620 --> 00:02:40.082 align:middle line:84%
interested in
spirituality, and magic,

00:02:40.082 --> 00:02:42.540 align:middle line:84%
and the esoteric side of things
because they want something

00:02:42.540 --> 00:02:43.340 align:middle line:90%
deeper.

00:02:43.340 --> 00:02:45.720 align:middle line:84%
They want a deeper experience
of life and understanding

00:02:45.720 --> 00:02:48.270 align:middle line:90%
what being alive means.

00:02:48.270 --> 00:02:51.960 align:middle line:84%
But they want to figure
that out on their own terms,

00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:55.350 align:middle line:84%
without it being imposed
by, like, a top-down church

00:02:55.350 --> 00:02:56.850 align:middle line:90%
or something like that usually.

00:02:56.850 --> 00:03:00.810 align:middle line:84%
So for that reason, I think
he's a fascinating person

00:03:00.810 --> 00:03:03.967 align:middle line:84%
for us to learn from and
just to understand ourselves,

00:03:03.967 --> 00:03:05.800 align:middle line:84%
and where we've been,
and where we're going.

00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:06.966 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I agree with that.

00:03:06.966 --> 00:03:09.120 align:middle line:84%
And to the point, Dean
Radin, a scientist

00:03:09.120 --> 00:03:11.880 align:middle line:84%
