both, especially

00:03:11.880 --> 00:03:13.650 align:middle line:84%
in the world of
quantum entanglement,

00:03:13.650 --> 00:03:16.930 align:middle line:84%
just came out with a new book
called "Real Magic," right?

00:03:16.930 --> 00:03:17.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:03:17.730 --> 00:03:19.830 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And now starting
to boldly, even embrace

00:03:19.830 --> 00:03:22.590 align:middle line:84%
the title, to bring the
two together in this world.

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:24.720 align:middle line:84%
So you're right
on target on that.

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:27.060 align:middle line:84%
I think one of the
problems is that people

00:03:27.060 --> 00:03:29.880 align:middle line:84%
have learned to be very
polarized in their thinking

00:03:29.880 --> 00:03:34.800 align:middle line:84%
and do not understand that these
characters, throughout history,

00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:38.580 align:middle line:84%
most of them were very
"colorful people."

00:03:38.580 --> 00:03:42.510 align:middle line:84%
And we say, how can someone
who would do such a thing also

00:03:42.510 --> 00:03:44.350 align:middle line:90%
come up with such a thing?

00:03:44.350 --> 00:03:45.975 align:middle line:10%
And so we're going
to get into some

00:03:45.975 --> 00:03:50.400 align:middle line:10%
of that, some of the
contrast within John

00:03:50.400 --> 00:03:53.250 align:middle line:10%
Dee, his personal character,
also Edward Kelley,

00:03:53.250 --> 00:03:55.500 align:middle line:10%
who he associated with, who
brought through, channeled

00:03:55.500 --> 00:03:57.720 align:middle line:10%
information and help
people understand

00:03:57.720 --> 00:03:59.220 align:middle line:10%
and get comfortable
with the notion,

00:03:59.220 --> 00:04:01.428 align:middle line:10%
you don't have to be a saint
to be brilliant and make

00:04:01.428 --> 00:04:03.120 align:middle line:10%
a contribution to society.

00:04:03.120 --> 00:04:04.860 align:middle line:90%
And that's true today as well.

00:04:04.860 --> 00:04:08.100 align:middle line:84%
So Francis Bacon,
wasn't Francis Bacon

00:04:08.100 --> 00:04:10.420 align:middle line:84%
more or less a
contemporary in the day?

00:04:10.420 --> 00:04:12.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: He was very
inspired by Dee.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:13.200 align:middle line:90%
Bacon came after Dee.

00:04:13.200 --> 00:04:17.160 align:middle line:84%
And Francis Bacon, of course,
created the Baconian method,

00:04:17.160 --> 00:04:19.709 align:middle line:90%
which became empirical science.

00:04:19.709 --> 00:04:22.360 align:middle line:84%
But he was very influenced
by Dee's thinking.

00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:26.850 align:middle line:84%
In fact, all of these guys were,
Francis Bacon, Rene Descartes,

00:04:26.850 --> 00:04:30.600 align:middle line:84%
the early scientists who became
the Royal Society in England.

00:04:30.600 --> 00:04:33.180 align:middle line:84%
All of the early
scientists were totally

00:04:33.180 --> 00:04:36.180 align:middle line:84%
fascinated by Dee's
work because Dee

00:04:36.180 --> 00:04:38.860 align:middle line:84%
was the person who had laid
the groundwork for science

00:04:38.860 --> 00:04:39.660 align:middle line:90%
to happen.

00:04:39.660 --> 00:04:42.090 align:middle line:84%
But they were also interested
in magic and the esoteric.

00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:45.020 align:middle line:84%
They were fascinated with
the idea of Rosicrucianism

00:04:45.020 --> 00:04:47.400 align:middle line:84%
and the Rosicrucian
brotherhood, which

00:04:47.400 --> 00:04:50.040 align:middle line:84%
was this kind of story
that was being told

00:04:50.040 --> 00:04:54.300 align:middle line:84%
around Europe that there was
this secret group of people

00:04:54.300 --> 00:04:57.270 align:middle line:84%
working to enlighten Europe,
to bring science to Europe,

00:04:57.270 --> 00:04:59.910 align:middle line:84%
to get Europe away from the
domination of the Church.

00:04:59.910 --> 00:05:01.639 align:middle line:90%
This all comes from Dee.

00:05:01.639 --> 00:05:03.180 align:middle line:84%
Previously, you
mentioned that people

00:05:03.180 --> 00:05:05.280 align:middle line:84%
are very polarized in
their thinking now.

00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:06.840 align:middle line:90%
It's either magic or science.

00:05:06.840 --> 00:05:09.000 align:middle line:84%
And neither of these
camps talk to each other.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:12.450 align:middle line:84%
And I come across
this myself a lot.

00:05:12.450 --> 00:05:15.190 align:middle line:84%
My way of seeing it is
the same that they did,

00:05:15.190 --> 00:05:18.220 align:middle line:84%
which is there's really
only one thing going on,

00:05:18.220 --> 00:05:20.330 align:middle line:84%
which is humanity's
quest for knowledge,

00:05:20.330 --> 00:05:23.870 align:middle line:84%
and humanity's quest to make
life better and learn more

00:05:23.870 --> 00:05:24.890 align:middle line:90%
about the universe.

00:05:24.890 --> 00:05:28.070 align:middle line:84%
And the spiritual side of
things is a tool for that.

00:05:28.070 --> 00:05:32.120 align:middle line:84%
The scientific, purely
materialistic science side,

00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:33.570 align:middle line:90%
is a tool to do that.

00:05:33.570 --> 00:05:35.420 align:middle line:84%
But these guys were
thinking in one

00:05:35.420 --> 00:05:37.025 align:middle line:84%
big-- they were big
picture thinkers.

00:05:37.025 --> 00:05:38.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's the type of
thinking that I really

00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:39.955 align:middle line:90%
want to encourage.

00:05:39.955 --> 00:05:41.330 align:middle line:84%
We should be
thinking, how can we

00:05:41.330 --> 00:05:43.880 align:middle line:84%
make the best possible
scientific advances,

00:05:43.880 --> 00:05:45.230 align:middle line:90%
with science on its own plain?

00:05:45.230 --> 00:05:49.640 align:middle line:84%
How can we also bring people
the best spiritual technologies,

00:05:49.640 --> 00:05:52.970 align:middle line:84%
if you will, to make
them happy and foster

00:05:52.970 --> 00:05:55.880 align:middle line:84%
a sense of connection, and
well-being, and happiness

00:05:55.880 --> 00:06:01.070 align:middle line:84%
in life, understanding life,
and putting it in context,

00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:02.640 align:middle line:90%
and what it really is?

00:06:02.640 --> 00:06:05.540 align:middle line:84%
So I'm very inspired
by those guys.

00:06:05.540 --> 00:06:06.340 align:middle line:90%
And they were--

00:06:06.340 --> 00:06:09.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you're the
classic new representation

00:06:09.470 --> 00:06:10.520 align:middle line:90%
of a Renaissance man.

00:06:10.520 --> 00:06:11.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Well, thank you.

00:06:11.050 --> 00:06:12.050 align:middle line:90%
I hope so.

00:06:12.050 --> 00:06:12.850 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You are.

00:06:12.850 --> 00:06:14.172 align:middle line:90%
You truly are.

00:06:14.172 --> 00:06:15.020 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:06:15.020 --> 00:06:17.120 align:middle line:84%
And so, at the same time,
when you look at Bacon,

00:06:17.120 --> 00:06:19.520 align:middle line:84%
for example, what
an incredible mind.

00:06:19.520 --> 00:06:22.490 align:middle line:84%
What many think to be
the actual, at least part

00:06:22.490 --> 00:06:25.910 align:middle line:84%
of, or if not, the better part
of the body of Shakespeare's

00:06:25.910 --> 00:06:28.130 align:middle line:90%
work, authorship of that.

00:06:28.130 --> 00:06:31.490 align:middle line:84%
I think that in
the intelligentsia

00:06:31.490 --> 00:06:33.710 align:middle line:90%
circles is kind of accepted.

00:06:33.710 --> 00:06:37.610 align:middle line:84%
But then also, under contract,
to rewrite the King James

00:06:37.610 --> 00:06:39.160 align:middle line:90%
version of the Bible.

00:06:39.160 --> 00:06:42.530 align:middle line:84%
