00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:59.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: But the language
is so beautiful.

00:08:59.540 --> 00:09:00.680 align:middle line:90%
The language is incredible.

00:09:00.680 --> 00:09:03.350 align:middle line:84%
And absolutely, there's
layered meaning in there.

00:09:03.350 --> 00:09:05.420 align:middle line:84%
You have to remember
that at this time period,

00:09:05.420 --> 00:09:06.350 align:middle line:90%
they didn't have TV.

00:09:06.350 --> 00:09:07.600 align:middle line:90%
They didn't have the internet.

00:09:07.600 --> 00:09:10.500 align:middle line:84%
So they loved to play
intellectual games.

00:09:10.500 --> 00:09:12.300 align:middle line:90%
I mean, people knew Greek.

00:09:12.300 --> 00:09:13.100 align:middle line:90%
They knew Latin.

00:09:13.100 --> 00:09:14.330 align:middle line:90%
They knew Hebrew.

00:09:14.330 --> 00:09:16.670 align:middle line:84%
They loved to play word
games, and puzzles,

00:09:16.670 --> 00:09:18.540 align:middle line:84%
and translate things
back and forth.

00:09:18.540 --> 00:09:21.930 align:middle line:84%
And that was how intelligent
people stimulated their minds.

00:09:21.930 --> 00:09:23.479 align:middle line:90%
And it was a common language.

00:09:23.479 --> 00:09:25.520 align:middle line:84%
So if you go back and look
at these things, which

00:09:25.520 --> 00:09:27.620 align:middle line:84%
I spent a lot of time
doing, writing this,

00:09:27.620 --> 00:09:31.276 align:middle line:84%
you see that you're dealing
with a much higher caliber

00:09:31.276 --> 00:09:32.150 align:middle line:90%
of thinking than is--

00:09:32.150 --> 00:09:32.950 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:09:32.950 --> 00:09:35.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: --common now.

00:09:35.990 --> 00:09:39.266 align:middle line:84%
In the sense is, if somebody was
watching our TV shows a hundred

00:09:39.266 --> 00:09:40.640 align:middle line:84%
years from now,
they're not going

00:09:40.640 --> 00:09:41.840 align:middle line:90%
to get all the little jokes.

00:09:41.840 --> 00:09:43.381 align:middle line:84%
They're not going
to get little winks

00:09:43.381 --> 00:09:44.960 align:middle line:90%
and pop cultural references.

00:09:44.960 --> 00:09:45.950 align:middle line:90%
It's the same there.

00:09:45.950 --> 00:09:48.680 align:middle line:84%
But the winks and the
pop culture references

00:09:48.680 --> 00:09:51.530 align:middle line:84%
are layers of spiritual
meaning, and Kabbalah,

00:09:51.530 --> 00:09:53.570 align:middle line:84%
and Rosicrucianism,
and esoterism,

00:09:53.570 --> 00:09:56.090 align:middle line:84%
and, as you said, things
that are there for people

00:09:56.090 --> 00:09:57.430 align:middle line:90%
who have eyes to see.

00:09:57.430 --> 00:09:59.512 align:middle line:84%
And it's thrilling to
go back and find it.

00:09:59.512 --> 00:10:01.970 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And it is, especially
when you open to the notion

00:10:01.970 --> 00:10:04.280 align:middle line:84%
that these men also had an
understanding of the cosmos.

00:10:04.280 --> 00:10:08.600 align:middle line:84%
And not just cosmology,
but astronomy-- astrology,

00:10:08.600 --> 00:10:11.180 align:middle line:84%
in Dee's case, and
understanding astrology.

00:10:11.180 --> 00:10:13.250 align:middle line:84%
So if we understand
that all of them

00:10:13.250 --> 00:10:20.030 align:middle line:84%
had a relative understanding
of our cosmological connection,

00:10:20.030 --> 00:10:22.874 align:middle line:84%
that we are universal
beings in a larger system,

00:10:22.874 --> 00:10:24.290 align:middle line:84%
then you start
reading these texts

00:10:24.290 --> 00:10:27.470 align:middle line:84%
and it starts looking
entirely different again.

00:10:27.470 --> 00:10:30.950 align:middle line:84%
So there are these
layers over layers.

00:10:30.950 --> 00:10:34.160 align:middle line:84%
And so that wraps
the Bacon part.

00:10:34.160 --> 00:10:37.190 align:middle line:84%
I just wanted to say that, yeah,
he did that under contract.

00:10:37.190 --> 00:10:39.150 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it can be used in
a fundamentalist way,

00:10:39.150 --> 00:10:41.090 align:middle line:84%
just like any of the
work of these guys.

00:10:41.090 --> 00:10:43.260 align:middle line:84%
Or, yes, it can be
absolutely magical.

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:46.410 align:middle line:84%
And that's up to us to develop a
nuance in our own understanding

00:10:46.410 --> 00:10:47.210 align:middle line:90%
and intelligence.

00:10:47.210 --> 00:10:48.168 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: It's important.

00:10:48.168 --> 00:10:49.680 align:middle line:84%
I mean, just to
wrap that up also.

00:10:49.680 --> 00:10:50.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:10:50.480 --> 00:10:51.854 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: It's
important to realize

00:10:51.854 --> 00:10:53.840 align:middle line:84%
that for exactly the
point that you mentioned,

00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.340 align:middle line:84%
which is people go
back to that text

00:10:55.340 --> 00:10:58.250 align:middle line:84%
and read it totally
literally, totally

00:10:58.250 --> 00:10:59.600 align:middle line:90%
as a fundamental reading.

00:10:59.600 --> 00:11:02.240 align:middle line:84%
What they're missing is
all the layers of metaphor,

00:11:02.240 --> 00:11:04.620 align:middle line:84%
and simile, and then
the artistic metaphors.

00:11:04.620 --> 00:11:06.860 align:middle line:84%
And then underneath,
the artistic metaphors,

00:11:06.860 --> 00:11:09.610 align:middle line:90%
the coded meanings and Kabbalah.

00:11:09.610 --> 00:11:11.486 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: The cosmic,
and all of it, yeah.

00:11:11.486 --> 00:11:12.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: It's
beautiful, you know.

00:11:12.860 --> 00:11:13.985 align:middle line:90%
So you look at Shakespeare.

00:11:13.985 --> 00:11:16.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, people can barely
read Shakespeare now.

00:11:16.220 --> 00:11:17.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:11:17.330 --> 00:11:19.538 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: You think about how
many layered meanings are

00:11:19.538 --> 00:11:20.960 align:middle line:84%
in Shakespeare
and you apply that

00:11:20.960 --> 00:11:23.150 align:middle line:84%
to the spiritual texts
of that time period.

00:11:23.150 --> 00:11:25.890 align:middle line:84%
And you can't make a
fundamentalist reading of it.

00:11:25.890 --> 00:11:26.690 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:11:26.690 --> 00:11:27.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: It's too surface.

00:11:27.740 --> 00:11:29.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:11:29.180 --> 00:11:33.060 align:middle line:84%
So you're attempting to bring
back the nuance into all of it.

00:11:33.060 --> 00:11:37.850 align:middle line:84%
So let's go into his
understanding, Elizabethan

00:11:37.850 --> 00:11:39.170 align:middle line:90%
hierarchy of the day.

00:11:39.170 --> 00:11:40.820 align:middle line:84%
They did believe
that there was a God.

00:11:40.820 --> 00:11:42.890 align:middle line:84%
There were angels, and
there were intermediaries,

00:11:42.890 --> 00:11:44.330 align:middle line:90%
and demons, and so forth.

00:11:44.330 --> 00:11:48.500 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about how John
Dee perceived that world.

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:49.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Absolutely.

00:11:49.550 --> 00:11:51.570 align:middle line:84%
So the Renaissance
view of the world

00:11:51.570 --> 00:11:54.680 align:middle line:84%
and the medieval view of the
world was basically this.

00:11:54.680 --> 00:11:56.510 align:middle line:90%
It's everything is one thing.

00:11:56.510 --> 00:12:01.010 align:middle line:84%
Everything that we see
that is perceivable is God.

00:12:01.010 --> 00:12:02.210 align:middle line:90%
And it's all one system.

00:12:02.210 --> 00:12:05.000 align:middle line:84%
And it works
functionally, perfectly.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:06.532 align:middle line:84%
And it's kind of
like a watch, where

00:12:06.532 --> 00:12:08.240 align:middle line:84%
all the gears are
wound up and everything

00:12:08.240 --> 00:12:09.115 align:middle line:90%
is working perfectly.

00:12:09.115 --> 00:12:11.330 align:middle line:84%
All the parts are
working perfectly.

00:12:11.330 --> 00:12:12.920 align:middle line:90%
And we've lost that.

00:12:12.920 --> 00:12:15.080 align:middle line:84%
Now, we see the world is
chaotic and meaningless.

00:12:15.080 --> 00:12:16.329 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Everything separate.

00:12:16.329 --> 00:12:17.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Everything separate.

00:12:17.680 --> 00:12:20.520 align:middle line:84%
I think that it's a flaw
in our consciousness,

00:12:20.520 --> 00:12:23.330 align:middle line:84%
rather than that our
understanding has changed.

00:12:23.330 --> 00:12:28.010 align:middle line:84%
But the way that people saw it
at the time was as a hierarchy.

00:12:28.010 --> 00:12:30.410 align:middle line:84%
You had God at the top,
followed by the angels, followed

00:12:30.410 --> 00:12:34.400 align:middle line:84%
by people, then followed by
animals, plants, minerals.

00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:37.800 align:middle line:84%
And then you got to the lower
spirits, the infernal realms.

00:12:37.800 --> 00:12:41.420 align:middle line:84%
But they saw everything
as interconnected.

00:12:41.420 --> 00:12:44.420 align:middle line:84%
Or holographic is the
best way to talk about it.

00:12:44.420 --> 00:12:46.580 align:middle line:84%
If you take a-- a
classic metaphor--

00:12:46.580 --> 00:12:49.280 align:middle line:84%
if you take a printed
hologram, not a projected one,

00:12:49.280 --> 00:12:51.750 align:middle line:84%
like a-- they used to have
hologram stickers that came in

00:12:51.750 --> 00:12:52.580 align:middle line:90%
and trading cards.

00:12:52.580 --> 00:12:52.970 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:12:52.970 --> 00:12:53.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:12:53.770 --> 00:12:56.660 align:middle line:84%
So you take one of those and
you cut it up into seven pieces.

00:12:56.660 --> 00:12:59.720 align:middle line:84%
Each of the smaller pieces will
contain the entire hologram.

00:12:59.720 --> 00:13:04.580 align:middle line:84%
That's how people saw
reality as working.

00:13:04.580 --> 00:13:07.610 align:middle line:84%
For instance, if man
was made in God's image,

00:13:07.610 --> 00:13:10.970 align:middle line:84%
then you could understand God
by understanding the human

00:13:10.970 --> 00:13:12.080 align:middle line:90%
and by seeing nature.

00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:13.790 align:middle line:84%
And all these things
were in resonance.

00:13:13.790 --> 00:13:16.160 align:middle line:84%
There's the classic
William Blake line,

00:13:16.160 --> 00:13:17.900 align:middle line:84%
I could see eternity
on a grain of sand.

00:13:17.900 --> 00:13:18.700 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:13:18.700 --> 00:13:21.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: That's basically
what they're talking about.

00:13:21.000 --> 00:13:24.660 align:middle line:84%
And that was a very comforting
worldview view for people.

00:13:24.660 --> 00:13:29.480 align:middle line:84%
It was a world where everything
made sense and was in order.

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:30.560 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:13:30.560 --> 00:13:33.260 align:middle line:84%
There was an inherent
orderliness to it.

00:13:33.260 --> 00:13:38.320 align:middle line:84%
And so that was also John Dee's
own internal belief system.

00:13:38.320 --> 00:13:39.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Uh-huh.

00:13:39.390 --> 00:13:40.190 align:middle line:90%
It was.

00:13:40.190 --> 00:13:43.140 align:middle line:84%
And it was the world view
of scientists at the time.

00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:44.840 align:middle line:90%
So now we think of science--

00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:48.830 align:middle line:84%
science had a very different
flavor at the time.

00:13:48.830 --> 00:13:50.630 align:middle line:84%
Now, we think of science
as moving forward

00:13:50.630 --> 00:13:53.840 align:middle line:90%
in time, as being progressive.

00:13:53.840 --> 00:13:56.150 align:middle line:84%
We're discovering new
things about the world.

00:13:56.150 --> 00:13:59.390 align:middle line:84%
In the Renaissance
period, the scientists

00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:01.340 align:middle line:84%
of the time, the
protoscientists,

00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:04.620 align:middle line:84%
believed that knowledge
was degrading over time,

00:14:04.620 --> 00:14:05.900 align:middle line:90%
instead of getting better.

00:14:05.900 --> 00:14:07.858 align:middle line:84%
They thought that
essentially perfect knowledge

00:14:07.858 --> 00:14:11.540 align:middle line:84%
had been given to mankind by
God in the Garden of Eden.

00:14:11.540 --> 00:14:14.270 align:middle line:84%
And then it was lost during
the fall of the Tower of Babel.

00:14:14.270 --> 00:14:16.590 align:middle line:84%
And more was lost during
the fall of Rome and Greece.

00:14:16.590 --> 00:14:18.590 align:middle line:84%
Remember, they were coming
out of the Dark Ages.

00:14:18.590 --> 00:14:20.091 align:middle line:84%
They were just
recovering knowledge.

00:14:20.091 --> 00:14:21.715 align:middle line:84%
They were just
recovering the knowledge

00:14:21.715 --> 00:14:23.180 align:middle line:90%
of the classical world.

00:14:23.180 --> 00:14:24.860 align:middle line:84%
So their view was
we have to go back

00:14:24.860 --> 00:14:26.340 align:middle line:90%
and recover what we've lost.

00:14:26.340 --> 00:14:28.089 align:middle line:84%
So they were looking
backwards and saying,

00:14:28.089 --> 00:14:30.950 align:middle line:84%
if only we can get to the
original knowledge that we had,

00:14:30.950 --> 00:14:32.100 align:middle line:90%
then we'll understand.

00:14:32.100 --> 00:14:34.620 align:middle line:84%
And John Dee's way of thinking
was even more extreme,

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:37.220 align:middle line:84%
which was, what if we can
connect directly to God

00:14:37.220 --> 00:14:38.140 align:middle line:90%
and ask him?

00:14:38.140 --> 00:14:39.723 align:middle line:84%
And if we can't do
that, then maybe we

00:14:39.723 --> 00:14:41.750 align:middle line:84%
can talk to God's
angels at least,

00:14:41.750 --> 00:14:45.170 align:middle line:84%
who might be a bit more ready
to have a conversation with us,

00:14:45.170 --> 00:14:46.700 align:middle line:90%
a bit closer to our level.

00:14:46.700 --> 00:14:48.600 align:middle line:84%
That was their way
of seeing things.

00:14:48.600 --> 00:14:51.320 align:middle line:84%
And so John Dee pursued
this quest with everything

00:14:51.320 --> 00:14:53.540 align:middle line:84%
that he had because
he thought that that

00:14:53.540 --> 00:14:55.610 align:middle line:84%
was the way to learning,
to getting more light,

00:14:55.610 --> 00:14:56.410 align:middle line:90%
more knowledge.

00:14:56.410 --> 00:14:58.820 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
perfectly logical.

00:14:58.820 --> 00:15:01.070 align:middle line:84%
I mean really, if
you take a babe

00:15:01.070 --> 00:15:02.870 align:middle line:84%
and let him grow
up naturally, this

00:15:02.870 --> 00:15:04.430 align:middle line:84%
is what we would
evolve to, is trying

00:15:04.430 --> 00:15:07.730 align:middle line:84%
to understand the invisible
principles that make something

00:15:07.730 --> 00:15:09.080 align:middle line:90%
so.

00:15:09.080 --> 00:15:11.150 align:middle line:84%
And so they were just,
I think, operating

00:15:11.150 --> 00:15:16.464 align:middle line:84%
on very natural principles
and asking that question.

00:15:16.464 --> 00:15:19.130 align:middle line:84%
And if you can bring it through,
through the hierarchy of beings

00:15:19.130 --> 00:15:21.690 align:middle line:84%
who inform, it makes
even more sense.

00:15:21.690 --> 00:15:23.660 align:middle line:84%
And then once
scientific materialism

00:15:23.660 --> 00:15:26.130 align:middle line:84%
became the religion, so
to speak, all of that's

00:15:26.130 --> 00:15:26.930 align:middle line:90%
been blocked.

00:15:26.930 --> 00:15:31.880 align:middle line:84%
And a massive amount
of real understanding

00:15:31.880 --> 00:15:35.630 align:middle line:84%
has been blocked at certain
levels, not at the top level,

00:15:35.630 --> 00:15:38.240 align:middle line:84%
but at that next tier down,
and the next tier down.

00:15:38.240 --> 00:15:39.740 align:middle line:84%
Because at the top
level, it seems

00:15:39.740 --> 00:15:41.660 align:middle line:84%
to be there are
always those who are

00:15:41.660 --> 00:15:45.530 align:middle line:84%
able to use both
realms of information,

00:15:45.530 --> 00:15:47.680 align:middle line:84%
all realms of information,
to their benefit

00:15:47.680 --> 00:15:47.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:15:47.930 --> 00:15:49.846 align:middle line:84%
I think that people who
are really intelligent

00:15:49.846 --> 00:15:51.890 align:middle line:84%
and naturally curious,
and who have not

00:15:51.890 --> 00:15:54.020 align:middle line:84%
lost their curiosity,
as so many of us

00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:58.070 align:middle line:84%
do because of how we're
educated and how our society is,

00:15:58.070 --> 00:15:59.436 align:middle line:90%
it's a natural way of thinking.

00:15:59.436 --> 00:16:01.310 align:middle line:84%
I think that people who
are naturally curious

00:16:01.310 --> 00:16:05.450 align:middle line:84%
see things in the
big picture way.

00:16:05.450 --> 00:16:07.670 align:middle line:84%
And they're just curious
about why are we alive?

00:16:07.670 --> 00:16:09.020 align:middle line:90%
Why are we here?

00:16:09.020 --> 00:16:10.790 align:middle line:84%
And they're not
afraid to look in lots

00:16:10.790 --> 00:16:12.560 align:middle line:84%
of different-- lots
of different areas

00:16:12.560 --> 00:16:14.070 align:middle line:84%
to try and understand
that question.

00:16:14.070 --> 00:16:14.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:16:14.870 --> 00:16:17.714 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's talk about the
other side of his personality.

00:16:17.714 --> 00:16:19.130 align:middle line:84%
He was all these
brilliant things.

00:16:19.130 --> 00:16:21.110 align:middle line:84%
Why was he in
prison for sorcery,

00:16:21.110 --> 00:16:22.780 align:middle line:90%
and conjuring, and all this?

00:16:22.780 --> 00:16:23.940 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:23.940 --> 00:16:28.640 align:middle line:84%
And in addition, how did this
affect his need to really put

00:16:28.640 --> 00:16:30.570 align:middle line:90%
forth science in the world?

00:16:30.570 --> 00:16:31.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:16:31.370 --> 00:16:34.250 align:middle line:84%
So Dee lived in a very
politically dangerous period

00:16:34.250 --> 00:16:35.810 align:middle line:90%
of history.

00:16:35.810 --> 00:16:38.660 align:middle line:84%
England at the time had
just left the Church.

00:16:38.660 --> 00:16:40.820 align:middle line:84%
They'd kind of done
their own Brexit.

00:16:40.820 --> 00:16:44.390 align:middle line:84%
And Henry had separated
the Anglican church

00:16:44.390 --> 00:16:46.350 align:middle line:90%
from the Catholic church.

00:16:46.350 --> 00:16:48.230 align:middle line:84%
And so what that
meant was there was

00:16:48.230 --> 00:16:52.070 align:middle line:84%
war, spiritual war between the
Catholics and the Protestants.

00:16:52.070 --> 00:16:55.880 align:middle line:84%
And Queen Mary, who was Henry's
daughter-- when Henry died,

00:16:55.880 --> 00:16:57.680 align:middle line:90%
Queen Mary became queen.

00:16:57.680 --> 00:16:58.610 align:middle line:90%
And she was Catholic.

00:16:58.610 --> 00:17:01.550 align:middle line:84%
And so there was kind of
a Catholic reconquering

00:17:01.550 --> 00:17:03.350 align:middle line:90%
of England.

00:17:03.350 --> 00:17:05.750 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
were burned as heretics

00:17:05.750 --> 00:17:08.089 align:middle line:84%
or imprisoned as heretics
who were Protestants.

00:17:08.089 --> 00:17:10.609 align:middle line:84%
And then when she
died, then Elizabeth

00:17:10.609 --> 00:17:12.880 align:middle line:90%
came in, who was Protestant.

00:17:12.880 --> 00:17:14.210 align:middle line:90%
And so it was back and forth.

00:17:14.210 --> 00:17:16.990 align:middle line:84%
We've seen that fight on
even to the modern day.

00:17:16.990 --> 00:17:19.700 align:middle line:84%
In Ireland, for instance,
this is a serious thing.

00:17:19.700 --> 00:17:23.920 align:middle line:84%
So Dee was a confidante
and a friend of Elizabeth.

00:17:23.920 --> 00:17:26.839 align:middle line:84%
And at one point had been
asked by her actually just

00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:30.140 align:middle line:84%
to do astrological
charts, of all things.

00:17:30.140 --> 00:17:31.290 align:middle line:90%
That was it.

00:17:31.290 --> 00:17:34.370 align:middle line:84%
He had been asked to draw
birth charts of Elizabeth

00:17:34.370 --> 00:17:35.245 align:middle line:90%
and potentially Mary.

00:17:35.245 --> 00:17:37.078 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Royalty has
always been interested

00:17:37.078 --> 00:17:38.630 align:middle line:84%
in astrology and
the big picture.

00:17:38.630 --> 00:17:40.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Of course, to this day.

00:17:40.430 --> 00:17:41.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: To this day.

00:17:41.780 --> 00:17:42.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: It's kind
of their thing.

00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:43.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:43.100 --> 00:17:43.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: It's big in England.

00:17:43.980 --> 00:17:45.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:17:45.050 --> 00:17:48.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: But he was
found out doing this.

00:17:48.720 --> 00:17:51.170 align:middle line:84%
And this was a
punishable offense.

00:17:51.170 --> 00:17:52.550 align:middle line:90%
It was considered sorcery.

00:17:52.550 --> 00:17:54.720 align:middle line:10%
They assumed that
Elizabeth and Dee

00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:57.800 align:middle line:10%
were conspiring to somehow
use magic to unseat

00:17:57.800 --> 00:17:59.840 align:middle line:10%
Queen Mary from the throne.

00:17:59.840 --> 00:18:03.020 align:middle line:84%
All he'd done was
draw up birth charts.

00:18:03.020 --> 00:18:06.650 align:middle line:84%
But for this, he was imprisoned
in the Tower of London,

00:18:06.650 --> 00:18:08.180 align:middle line:90%
with other Protestant heretics.

00:18:08.180 --> 00:18:08.990 align:middle line:90%
He was tortured.

00:18:08.990 --> 00:18:12.930 align:middle line:84%
He was forced to reconvene
to Catholicism publicly.

00:18:12.930 --> 00:18:13.760 align:middle line:90%
It was a mess.

00:18:13.760 --> 00:18:16.730 align:middle line:84%
And he was in that situation
until the regime changed

00:18:16.730 --> 00:18:18.890 align:middle line:90%
and Elizabeth became queen.

00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:21.680 align:middle line:84%
So it definitely
changed his attitude.

00:18:21.680 --> 00:18:23.600 align:middle line:84%
Before that, you
have to remember,

00:18:23.600 --> 00:18:26.030 align:middle line:84%
this person was a pure
academic, somebody who was just

00:18:26.030 --> 00:18:27.050 align:middle line:90%
seeking after knowledge.

00:18:27.050 --> 00:18:30.380 align:middle line:84%
He truly believed in bringing
higher knowledge to humanity.

00:18:30.380 --> 00:18:33.540 align:middle line:84%
He truly believed
in England and doing

00:18:33.540 --> 00:18:34.790 align:middle line:90%
what was best for his country.

00:18:34.790 --> 00:18:36.320 align:middle line:90%
And I think it was very--

00:18:36.320 --> 00:18:39.000 align:middle line:90%


00:18:39.000 --> 00:18:42.967 align:middle line:84%
it definitely changed him
to get that treatment.

00:18:42.967 --> 00:18:44.300 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: How did it change him?

00:18:44.300 --> 00:18:45.925 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Well, I think
as you mentioned,

00:18:45.925 --> 00:18:49.037 align:middle line:84%
he spent a lot of time trying
to resuscitate his reputation,

00:18:49.037 --> 00:18:50.120 align:middle line:90%
until the end of his life.

00:18:50.120 --> 00:18:52.772 align:middle line:84%
He was trying to convince
people that he was a true--

00:18:52.772 --> 00:18:53.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He wasn't a nutter.

00:18:53.980 --> 00:18:54.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: --Christian.

00:18:54.260 --> 00:18:55.700 align:middle line:90%
He was a true scientist.

00:18:55.700 --> 00:18:57.300 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't a black magician.

00:18:57.300 --> 00:18:58.100 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:18:58.100 --> 00:19:00.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: And they were
constantly accusing him of that.

00:19:00.740 --> 00:19:02.390 align:middle line:84%
The irony is that
the other side,

00:19:02.390 --> 00:19:04.640 align:middle line:84%
on Queen Mary's side
and the Catholic side,

00:19:04.640 --> 00:19:07.944 align:middle line:84%
they were using black magic
to try and get their goals,

00:19:07.944 --> 00:19:09.860 align:middle line:84%
and to attack the queen--
and Queen Elizabeth,

00:19:09.860 --> 00:19:10.790 align:middle line:90%
and all of this.

00:19:10.790 --> 00:19:12.500 align:middle line:90%
So it was a messy time.

00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:13.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Anyway, OK.

00:19:13.610 --> 00:19:15.950 align:middle line:84%
Let's talk about math,
and his love of math

00:19:15.950 --> 00:19:18.890 align:middle line:84%
and how this feeds into his
esoteric understanding of life

00:19:18.890 --> 00:19:19.690 align:middle line:90%
even.

00:19:19.690 --> 00:19:20.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Oh, it's fascinating.

00:19:20.570 --> 00:19:22.520 align:middle line:84%
I mean people hear math
and they immediately--

00:19:22.520 --> 00:19:23.870 align:middle line:90%
it's like an allergic reaction.

00:19:23.870 --> 00:19:25.070 align:middle line:90%
Oh, God.

00:19:25.070 --> 00:19:27.195 align:middle line:84%
But when you understand it
the way that Dee saw it,

00:19:27.195 --> 00:19:29.120 align:middle line:90%
it becomes totally fascinating.

00:19:29.120 --> 00:19:33.330 align:middle line:84%
Dee thought that math was the
language that God uses to talk.

00:19:33.330 --> 00:19:34.131 align:middle line:90%
It was that simple.

00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:35.463 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: He's not the only one.

00:19:35.463 --> 00:19:36.900 align:middle line:90%
A lot of people think this now.

00:19:36.900 --> 00:19:37.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:19:37.700 --> 00:19:42.590 align:middle line:84%
And he basically-- again, with
the backdrop of religious wars,

00:19:42.590 --> 00:19:44.320 align:middle line:84%
people fighting
over who's right,

00:19:44.320 --> 00:19:46.370 align:middle line:84%
Dee wanted to figure out,
well, what's the truth?

00:19:46.370 --> 00:19:48.470 align:middle line:84%
And the conclusion that he came
to, which I think is completely

00:19:48.470 --> 00:19:50.810 align:middle line:84%
accurate, is that-- and
I think more scientists

00:19:50.810 --> 00:19:52.520 align:middle line:84%
and mathematicians
would agree with it--

00:19:52.520 --> 00:19:54.521 align:middle line:84%
is that if we really want
to understand reality,

00:19:54.521 --> 00:19:56.061 align:middle line:84%
if we want to
understand what's true,

00:19:56.061 --> 00:19:57.530 align:middle line:84%
you have to go to
pure mathematics

00:19:57.530 --> 00:19:59.480 align:middle line:90%
because you can't fake it.

00:19:59.480 --> 00:20:00.650 align:middle line:90%
The numbers don't lie.

00:20:00.650 --> 00:20:01.520 align:middle line:90%
Statistics might.

00:20:01.520 --> 00:20:04.010 align:middle line:90%
But pure mathematics don't.

00:20:04.010 --> 00:20:05.600 align:middle line:84%
So he thought
that-- for instance,

00:20:05.600 --> 00:20:08.000 align:middle line:84%
that the fact that there are
mathematical constants that

00:20:08.000 --> 00:20:10.880 align:middle line:84%
repeat throughout nature,
like pi, phi, and e, and all

00:20:10.880 --> 00:20:13.334 align:middle line:84%
these things, the Fibonacci
sequence-- the fact

00:20:13.334 --> 00:20:14.750 align:middle line:84%
that there are
repeating sequences

00:20:14.750 --> 00:20:19.650 align:middle line:84%
shows that there's some type of
inherent structure to reality.

00:20:19.650 --> 00:20:22.840 align:middle line:90%
I mean, you can't deny that.

00:20:22.840 --> 00:20:26.890 align:middle line:84%
So he wrote the introduction to
a book called the "Elements,"

00:20:26.890 --> 00:20:29.500 align:middle line:84%
by Euclid, which was the
first big textbook on higher

00:20:29.500 --> 00:20:32.830 align:middle line:84%
mathematics that was brought to
the public, in which he says,

00:20:32.830 --> 00:20:38.800 align:middle line:84%
that mathematics is not just
a way of counting dollars

00:20:38.800 --> 00:20:41.440 align:middle line:84%
or pounds at the
time in England.

00:20:41.440 --> 00:20:42.580 align:middle line:90%
It's a way of--

00:20:42.580 --> 00:20:43.510 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Quid.

00:20:43.510 --> 00:20:44.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah, exactly.

00:20:44.740 --> 00:20:46.570 align:middle line:84%
It's a way of
understanding reality.

00:20:46.570 --> 00:20:48.130 align:middle line:84%
And it's a way of
talking to God.

00:20:48.130 --> 00:20:50.140 align:middle line:84%
And he actually
says in that book--

00:20:50.140 --> 00:20:53.950 align:middle line:84%
it's so crazy-- he says that we
may have come to a time period

00:20:53.950 --> 00:20:56.230 align:middle line:84%
where there is no longer
any big revelations.

00:20:56.230 --> 00:20:59.260 align:middle line:84%
All the big revelations came to
the desert prophets long ago.

00:20:59.260 --> 00:21:01.951 align:middle line:84%
But even if we can't get divine
revelations, we have math.

00:21:01.951 --> 00:21:03.700 align:middle line:84%
And maybe that's just
as good because it's

00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:06.552 align:middle line:84%
a way of understanding
what reality actually is.

00:21:06.552 --> 00:21:09.010 align:middle line:84%
And again, I mean, I think it's
an out there way to put it.

00:21:09.010 --> 00:21:10.926 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think
mathematicians or scientists

00:21:10.926 --> 00:21:12.520 align:middle line:90%
would argue against that.

00:21:12.520 --> 00:21:14.650 align:middle line:84%
It's just said in a
slightly different language.

00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:16.274 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yeah, I
would agree with you.

00:21:16.274 --> 00:21:20.130 align:middle line:84%
And maybe that was also part
of his love of astrology,

00:21:20.130 --> 00:21:22.210 align:middle line:84%
the pure mathematical
movement of the cosmos

00:21:22.210 --> 00:21:23.600 align:middle line:84%
and its interface
with the Earth.

00:21:23.600 --> 00:21:24.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Mm-hmm.

00:21:24.400 --> 00:21:25.360 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:21:25.360 --> 00:21:27.370 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Math again.

00:21:27.370 --> 00:21:31.790 align:middle line:84%
Also his work was influenced
by Hermes and the "Corpus

00:21:31.790 --> 00:21:32.639 align:middle line:90%
Hermeticum."

00:21:32.639 --> 00:21:34.430 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you can talk
about that a little bit.

00:21:34.430 --> 00:21:35.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:21:35.230 --> 00:21:38.800 align:middle line:84%
So the hermetic texts are kind
of an underground tradition

00:21:38.800 --> 00:21:40.780 align:middle line:84%
of literature,
that's been around

00:21:40.780 --> 00:21:43.610 align:middle line:84%
since the death of Christ
and before that even.

00:21:43.610 --> 00:21:44.410 align:middle line:90%
There were--

00:21:44.410 --> 00:21:45.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Probably way before.

00:21:45.430 --> 00:21:45.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:21:45.760 --> 00:21:47.010 align:middle line:90%
I mean, it's a crazy field.

00:21:47.010 --> 00:21:50.815 align:middle line:84%
There is a hermetic text from
Egypt, from the Coptics, from--

00:21:50.815 --> 00:21:53.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the Egyptians
said from Atlantis.

00:21:53.010 --> 00:21:55.570 align:middle line:84%
That's down from there, to the
Egyptians, to the Coptics--

00:21:55.570 --> 00:21:56.370 align:middle line:90%
to--

00:21:56.370 --> 00:21:57.120 align:middle line:90%
yeah.

00:21:57.120 --> 00:21:57.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:21:57.920 --> 00:22:01.270 align:middle line:84%
And it's an interesting
literary genre.

00:22:01.270 --> 00:22:04.000 align:middle line:84%
And it's a literary genre
where there are claims

00:22:04.000 --> 00:22:05.082 align:middle line:90%
like that made, Atlantis.

00:22:05.082 --> 00:22:06.790 align:middle line:84%
And then there also
claims where-- it was

00:22:06.790 --> 00:22:08.336 align:middle line:90%
written by Hermes Trismegistus.

00:22:08.336 --> 00:22:10.960 align:middle line:84%
This turns out to be a pen name,
that a lot of different people

00:22:10.960 --> 00:22:11.760 align:middle line:90%
shared.

00:22:11.760 --> 00:22:14.260 align:middle line:84%
There was probably never
one Hermes Trismegistus.

00:22:14.260 --> 00:22:17.080 align:middle line:84%
But it's a genre
of literature that

00:22:17.080 --> 00:22:19.960 align:middle line:84%
looks at reality in the way that
I've been saying, as if it's

00:22:19.960 --> 00:22:23.470 align:middle line:84%
one thing, one substance, and
can be understood directly,

00:22:23.470 --> 00:22:26.260 align:middle line:84%
without a intermediary
of a church.

00:22:26.260 --> 00:22:28.630 align:middle line:90%
And that's a dangerous idea.

00:22:28.630 --> 00:22:31.690 align:middle line:84%
It was a dangerous idea then,
that you could understand

00:22:31.690 --> 00:22:33.940 align:middle line:84%
reality through experiment
and direct revelation,

00:22:33.940 --> 00:22:36.470 align:middle line:84%
instead of a church hierarchy
telling you what to believe.

00:22:36.470 --> 00:22:37.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
what I love about it.

00:22:37.360 --> 00:22:38.484 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: It's dangerous now.

00:22:38.484 --> 00:22:39.880 align:middle line:90%
That's a really dangerous idea.

00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:40.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Love it.

00:22:40.430 --> 00:22:42.179 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: That's really
what the Hermetica--

00:22:42.179 --> 00:22:44.530 align:middle line:84%
I mean it's an incredibly
complex literary genre.

00:22:44.530 --> 00:22:44.860 align:middle line:90%
But that's--

00:22:44.860 --> 00:22:44.935 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it is.

00:22:44.935 --> 00:22:46.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: --what it comes down to.

00:22:46.510 --> 00:22:46.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:22:46.780 --> 00:22:48.654 align:middle line:84%
So he was influenced by
that because that was

00:22:48.654 --> 00:22:50.670 align:middle line:90%
his own approach, essentially.

00:22:50.670 --> 00:22:52.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Absolutely.

00:22:52.120 --> 00:22:55.000 align:middle line:84%
It formed the intellectual
underpinnings, not just of

00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:57.820 align:middle line:84%
his approach, but of the
people who-- the Rosicrucians,

00:22:57.820 --> 00:22:59.550 align:middle line:84%
the people who became
the scientists.

00:22:59.550 --> 00:23:00.580 align:middle line:84%
If you think of it
this time, there's

00:23:00.580 --> 00:23:02.890 align:middle line:84%
two big competing schools
of thought, the Catholics

00:23:02.890 --> 00:23:04.180 align:middle line:90%
and Protestants.

00:23:04.180 --> 00:23:07.570 align:middle line:84%
And they're at war, these giant
titans fighting each other.

00:23:07.570 --> 00:23:10.750 align:middle line:84%
And in between, there was this
little third option, which

00:23:10.750 --> 00:23:12.160 align:middle line:90%
is the hermetics, who are--

00:23:12.160 --> 00:23:13.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: And the Rosicrucians.

00:23:13.090 --> 00:23:13.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:23:13.690 --> 00:23:15.180 align:middle line:84%
Well, why don't we just
actually do an experiment

00:23:15.180 --> 00:23:17.221 align:middle line:84%
to figure out what reality
is instead of fighting

00:23:17.221 --> 00:23:18.670 align:middle line:90%
over what we think it is.

00:23:18.670 --> 00:23:22.642 align:middle line:84%
And it was that underground
that became modern science.

00:23:22.642 --> 00:23:24.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And he
wrote, ultimately,

00:23:24.100 --> 00:23:25.220 align:middle line:90%
the "Monas Hieroglyphica?"

00:23:25.220 --> 00:23:26.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:23:26.020 --> 00:23:28.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And tell us what that
is and what its influence was.

00:23:28.850 --> 00:23:30.350 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: So the
"Monas Hieroglyphica"

00:23:30.350 --> 00:23:32.920 align:middle line:90%
was a short text.

00:23:32.920 --> 00:23:36.040 align:middle line:84%
It's maybe 10 pages
long, 15 pages long.

00:23:36.040 --> 00:23:38.740 align:middle line:10%
And it's a book that's
synthesized everything

00:23:38.740 --> 00:23:43.030 align:middle line:10%
that he knew about the
hermetics, alchemy, astrology,

00:23:43.030 --> 00:23:46.010 align:middle line:10%
science, mathematics
into one text,

00:23:46.010 --> 00:23:47.950 align:middle line:10%
that he said has the
key to the mysteries

00:23:47.950 --> 00:23:50.020 align:middle line:10%
and explains all of reality.

00:23:50.020 --> 00:23:52.420 align:middle line:84%
And also explains
the key to alchemy,

00:23:52.420 --> 00:23:55.430 align:middle line:84%
which is what all the monarchs
in Europe wanted at this time.

00:23:55.430 --> 00:23:57.610 align:middle line:84%
And so he brought this
to several monarchs,

00:23:57.610 --> 00:23:59.710 align:middle line:84%
including the Holy Roman
Emperor Maximilian I.

00:23:59.710 --> 00:24:01.180 align:middle line:90%
He brought it to Elizabeth.

00:24:01.180 --> 00:24:04.092 align:middle line:84%
And he told them, this book
has all the secrets of alchemy.

00:24:04.092 --> 00:24:06.550 align:middle line:84%
And they said, oh, so you mean
you can make us as much gold

00:24:06.550 --> 00:24:07.450 align:middle line:90%
as we want.

00:24:07.450 --> 00:24:09.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Always they
go to the lowest place.

00:24:09.360 --> 00:24:11.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: He said, well, no,
but I can enlighten you.

00:24:11.620 --> 00:24:12.995 align:middle line:84%
It'll bring you
spiritual wisdom.

00:24:12.995 --> 00:24:16.465 align:middle line:84%
And their response was, OK,
next, next, next, please.

00:24:16.465 --> 00:24:17.890 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Oh, exactly.

00:24:17.890 --> 00:24:22.000 align:middle line:84%
OK, so how did he get into the
good graces of Queen Elizabeth

00:24:22.000 --> 00:24:25.390 align:middle line:84%
and become such a
valued advisor to her?

00:24:25.390 --> 00:24:29.020 align:middle line:84%
And what was the nature of the
kind of advice he would render?

00:24:29.020 --> 00:24:30.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: It's a
fascinating story.

00:24:30.770 --> 00:24:35.020 align:middle line:84%
So he was a loyalist to
Elizabeth during Mary's reign.

00:24:35.020 --> 00:24:38.350 align:middle line:84%
And was brought in basically
as a security guard,

00:24:38.350 --> 00:24:41.200 align:middle line:84%
as a magical security
guard to Elizabeth's court.

00:24:41.200 --> 00:24:44.440 align:middle line:84%
As soon as she seized
power, the outgoing regime

00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:49.205 align:middle line:84%
was employing all these
Catholic sorcerers, in a sense.

00:24:49.205 --> 00:24:50.830 align:middle line:84%
They were sticking--
it's a real story.

00:24:50.830 --> 00:24:51.954 align:middle line:90%
They were sticking voodoo--

00:24:51.954 --> 00:24:53.590 align:middle line:84%
making voodoo doll
of her, sticking--

00:24:53.590 --> 00:24:58.360 align:middle line:84%
all this crazy stuff, creating
propaganda campaigns to make

00:24:58.360 --> 00:24:59.590 align:middle line:90%
her look bad.

00:24:59.590 --> 00:25:01.720 align:middle line:84%
Doing all kinds of crazy
magical things, to try

00:25:01.720 --> 00:25:03.370 align:middle line:90%
and take down her court.

00:25:03.370 --> 00:25:07.300 align:middle line:84%
And so Dee was brought in
to counteract this and be

00:25:07.300 --> 00:25:08.940 align:middle line:90%
their kind of magical advisor.

00:25:08.940 --> 00:25:11.530 align:middle line:84%
But he also became the
scientific advisor.

00:25:11.530 --> 00:25:13.600 align:middle line:84%
He became the
mathematical advisor.

00:25:13.600 --> 00:25:17.650 align:middle line:84%
He was one of the people who
is instrumental in setting up

00:25:17.650 --> 00:25:20.660 align:middle line:84%
the British security services,
which later became MI5 and MI6,

00:25:20.660 --> 00:25:21.826 align:middle line:90%
with Sir Francis Walsingham.

00:25:21.826 --> 00:25:23.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, we'll
talk about too.

00:25:23.420 --> 00:25:25.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Elizabeth
referred to him as 007.

00:25:25.140 --> 00:25:28.010 align:middle line:84%
That's the code number
which became James Bond.

00:25:28.010 --> 00:25:30.680 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And Ian Fleming was
tapped into this knowledge.

00:25:30.680 --> 00:25:31.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:25:31.480 --> 00:25:33.090 align:middle line:90%
Ian Fleming was a fascinating--

00:25:33.090 --> 00:25:34.590 align:middle line:84%
of course, the
author of James Bond,

00:25:34.590 --> 00:25:36.180 align:middle line:90%
who was a fascinating guy.

00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:41.310 align:middle line:84%
He was employed by, I believe,
MI6 or MI5 during World War II,

00:25:41.310 --> 00:25:44.170 align:middle line:84%
to create propaganda campaigns
to throw off the Nazi war

00:25:44.170 --> 00:25:44.970 align:middle line:90%
effort.

00:25:44.970 --> 00:25:49.230 align:middle line:84%
As part of this, he
employed Alister Crowley

00:25:49.230 --> 00:25:54.400 align:middle line:84%
to falsify astrological
charts for Rudolf Hess,

00:25:54.400 --> 00:25:57.340 align:middle line:84%
so that he would be
confused-- it's so strange.

00:25:57.340 --> 00:25:58.860 align:middle line:90%
So he would do wrong--

00:25:58.860 --> 00:25:59.860 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Bad decisions.

00:25:59.860 --> 00:26:01.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Bad decisions, right.

00:26:01.140 --> 00:26:02.480 align:middle line:90%
They never implemented the plan.

00:26:02.480 --> 00:26:06.120 align:middle line:84%
But Fleming was so taken with
this world of the occult that

00:26:06.120 --> 00:26:09.510 align:middle line:84%
when he created James Bond,
he named his creation 007.

00:26:09.510 --> 00:26:12.600 align:middle line:84%
And he also patterned Blofeld,
who's the head of Spectre,

00:26:12.600 --> 00:26:14.500 align:middle line:84%
off Crowley, the
ultimate bad guy.

00:26:14.500 --> 00:26:15.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:26:15.420 --> 00:26:16.480 align:middle line:90%
It is fascinating.

00:26:16.480 --> 00:26:17.938 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: The one
with the white cat.

00:26:17.938 --> 00:26:19.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:26:19.480 --> 00:26:20.280 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:26:20.280 --> 00:26:21.488 align:middle line:90%
You can't make this stuff up.

00:26:21.488 --> 00:26:22.740 align:middle line:90%
It has to be born somewhere.

00:26:22.740 --> 00:26:24.870 align:middle line:84%
And apparently it
goes back to John Dee.

00:26:24.870 --> 00:26:29.790 align:middle line:84%
So John Dee, how did he
influence the development

00:26:29.790 --> 00:26:32.910 align:middle line:90%
of the field of intelligence?

00:26:32.910 --> 00:26:35.484 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: So during
this time, they were--

00:26:35.484 --> 00:26:36.900 align:middle line:84%
England, you have
to remember, was

00:26:36.900 --> 00:26:39.930 align:middle line:84%
a tiny, impoverished
country, that

00:26:39.930 --> 00:26:41.750 align:middle line:90%
was at the point of the stick--

00:26:41.750 --> 00:26:44.970 align:middle line:84%
at the point of a stick
of the Catholic block.

00:26:44.970 --> 00:26:46.980 align:middle line:84%
All of Europe was Catholic,
outside of England

00:26:46.980 --> 00:26:48.300 align:middle line:90%
and the Netherlands.

00:26:48.300 --> 00:26:51.626 align:middle line:84%
And they were at
extreme disadvantage.

00:26:51.626 --> 00:26:52.500 align:middle line:90%
People were starving.

00:26:52.500 --> 00:26:54.430 align:middle line:84%
They had very few
material resources.

00:26:54.430 --> 00:26:57.300 align:middle line:84%
So Elizabeth was
doing everything

00:26:57.300 --> 00:27:00.000 align:middle line:84%
she could to keep
her country going

00:27:00.000 --> 00:27:02.070 align:middle line:90%
and make sure that it survived.

00:27:02.070 --> 00:27:05.160 align:middle line:84%
And during this time, they did
set up the British intelligence

00:27:05.160 --> 00:27:07.840 align:middle line:90%
services to counteract--

00:27:07.840 --> 00:27:09.960 align:middle line:84%
you know, as part
of the war effort.

00:27:09.960 --> 00:27:12.360 align:middle line:84%
And Dee's job during
this-- it was set up

00:27:12.360 --> 00:27:14.190 align:middle line:90%
by Francis Walsingham.

00:27:14.190 --> 00:27:17.250 align:middle line:84%
And as an aside, by the way,
just for some more context,

00:27:17.250 --> 00:27:19.170 align:middle line:84%
England was so
poor at this time,

00:27:19.170 --> 00:27:21.870 align:middle line:84%
people often accused
Dee of dying of poverty.

00:27:21.870 --> 00:27:24.360 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, how he couldn't
have been such a good magician.

00:27:24.360 --> 00:27:28.320 align:middle line:84%
The reality was that everyone
was poor at this time.

00:27:28.320 --> 00:27:31.140 align:middle line:84%
Francis Walsingham, who started
the intelligence services,

00:27:31.140 --> 00:27:32.550 align:middle line:84%
financed it out
of his own pocket

00:27:32.550 --> 00:27:34.675 align:middle line:84%
because he couldn't get
paid by Elizabeth to do it.

00:27:34.675 --> 00:27:36.510 align:middle line:84%
That's how strapped
the government was.

00:27:36.510 --> 00:27:40.830 align:middle line:10%
So Dee's role in this
was getting information.

00:27:40.830 --> 00:27:42.540 align:middle line:10%
They were very
interested in collecting

00:27:42.540 --> 00:27:45.220 align:middle line:10%
all of the occult information
that was available in Europe.

00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:47.700 align:middle line:84%
He was sent to discover
this book called

00:27:47.700 --> 00:27:51.130 align:middle line:84%
the "Steganographia," to hunt
for it throughout Europe.

00:27:51.130 --> 00:27:55.050 align:middle line:84%
It was a grimoire that
promised to not only have

00:27:55.050 --> 00:27:58.800 align:middle line:84%
the secret of cryptography,
but also to contain

00:27:58.800 --> 00:28:00.990 align:middle line:84%
a magical ritual that
would allow somebody

00:28:00.990 --> 00:28:03.090 align:middle line:84%
to spy on somebody
else in the country,

00:28:03.090 --> 00:28:05.580 align:middle line:84%
to call up a vision of
what someone was doing.

00:28:05.580 --> 00:28:07.954 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's what
I was going to bring up next.

00:28:07.954 --> 00:28:09.600 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they were
doing real spying,

00:28:09.600 --> 00:28:11.072 align:middle line:84%
real remote viewing,
so to speak.

00:28:11.072 --> 00:28:12.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Remote viewing.

00:28:12.030 --> 00:28:12.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:28:12.570 --> 00:28:15.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Basically that's what
they were trying to figure out.

00:28:15.160 --> 00:28:15.960 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Which makes
sense, because if you

00:28:15.960 --> 00:28:18.420 align:middle line:84%
don't have any resources, you
can't necessarily send people

00:28:18.420 --> 00:28:21.630 align:middle line:84%
on the ground, get them
on a train, or a donkey,

00:28:21.630 --> 00:28:24.280 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, to get where they
need to go to do the research.

00:28:24.280 --> 00:28:25.740 align:middle line:90%
So you just go direct, right?

00:28:25.740 --> 00:28:26.540 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:28:26.540 --> 00:28:29.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so did he have
some success, as far as you

00:28:29.670 --> 00:28:32.310 align:middle line:84%
can tell, by way of
training other agents

00:28:32.310 --> 00:28:34.140 align:middle line:90%
or being able to view?

00:28:34.140 --> 00:28:36.690 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: As far as I
know, he never actually

00:28:36.690 --> 00:28:37.690 align:middle line:90%
directly engaged in it.

00:28:37.690 --> 00:28:38.490 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:28:38.490 --> 00:28:40.115 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: They sent
him to find the book.

00:28:40.115 --> 00:28:42.090 align:middle line:84%
What he did do is he
took the techniques

00:28:42.090 --> 00:28:45.150 align:middle line:84%
and then applied them
to his later work,

00:28:45.150 --> 00:28:46.980 align:middle line:84%
scrying angels and
talking to angels.

00:28:46.980 --> 00:28:49.680 align:middle line:84%
That went into his work,
tried to basically remote view

00:28:49.680 --> 00:28:51.720 align:middle line:84%
angels, if you want to
put it in those terms.

00:28:51.720 --> 00:28:52.520 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:28:52.520 --> 00:28:55.650 align:middle line:84%
OK, so it's not surprising that
John Dee had some detractors

00:28:55.650 --> 00:28:56.640 align:middle line:90%
and even enemies.

00:28:56.640 --> 00:28:58.910 align:middle line:84%
Who were John Prestall
and Vincent Murphyn?

00:28:58.910 --> 00:29:00.870 align:middle line:84%
And why did they try
to take him down?

00:29:00.870 --> 00:29:01.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:29:01.670 --> 00:29:05.542 align:middle line:84%
So these two gentlemen were
two very shady characters.

00:29:05.542 --> 00:29:06.375 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Gentlemen.

00:29:06.375 --> 00:29:06.690 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGH]

00:29:06.690 --> 00:29:07.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:29:07.490 --> 00:29:12.855 align:middle line:84%
They were fake
alchemists and sorcerers.

00:29:12.855 --> 00:29:13.980 align:middle line:90%
There is a real difference.

00:29:13.980 --> 00:29:15.688 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's really
important to make

00:29:15.688 --> 00:29:18.025 align:middle line:84%
this distinction because
it's important now also.

00:29:18.025 --> 00:29:19.650 align:middle line:84%
There is a real
difference between what

00:29:19.650 --> 00:29:22.890 align:middle line:84%
we might, by way of
oversimplification,

00:29:22.890 --> 00:29:24.750 align:middle line:90%
call high magic and low magic.

00:29:24.750 --> 00:29:27.750 align:middle line:84%
High magic is totally
about understanding

00:29:27.750 --> 00:29:28.840 align:middle line:90%
God in the universe.

00:29:28.840 --> 00:29:29.886 align:middle line:90%
And it's like science.

00:29:29.886 --> 00:29:31.260 align:middle line:84%
It's about becoming
spiritually--

00:29:31.260 --> 00:29:32.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Sensing the
nature of reality.

00:29:32.430 --> 00:29:33.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Absolutely.

00:29:33.180 --> 00:29:34.740 align:middle line:84%
And trying to become
more enlightened

00:29:34.740 --> 00:29:35.940 align:middle line:90%
and a better person.

00:29:35.940 --> 00:29:36.930 align:middle line:90%
That's it.

00:29:36.930 --> 00:29:38.250 align:middle line:90%
That's high magic.

00:29:38.250 --> 00:29:42.720 align:middle line:84%
And low magic is trying to
use magic to get your way,

00:29:42.720 --> 00:29:44.510 align:middle line:90%
or hurt somebody, or get money.

00:29:44.510 --> 00:29:45.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Have power.

00:29:45.430 --> 00:29:46.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Totally.

00:29:46.230 --> 00:29:50.247 align:middle line:84%
It's all these
very vulgar things,

00:29:50.247 --> 00:29:52.080 align:middle line:84%
that anyone who was
interested in high magic

00:29:52.080 --> 00:29:53.970 align:middle line:84%
would just not be
interested in at all

00:29:53.970 --> 00:29:56.130 align:middle line:90%
and be allergic to, essentially.

00:29:56.130 --> 00:29:58.800 align:middle line:84%
But there are lots of people
who are interested in it.

00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:00.190 align:middle line:90%
And there were at the time.

00:30:00.190 --> 00:30:03.600 align:middle line:84%
And these two gentlemen,
Murphyn and Prestall,

00:30:03.600 --> 00:30:08.010 align:middle line:84%
were employed by the
outgoing Catholic regime,

00:30:08.010 --> 00:30:09.660 align:middle line:84%
and also during
Queen Mary's reign,

00:30:09.660 --> 00:30:13.900 align:middle line:84%
if I remember correctly, to
attack Elizabeth and Dee using

00:30:13.900 --> 00:30:14.700 align:middle line:90%
magic.

00:30:14.700 --> 00:30:17.040 align:middle line:90%
And they fought dirty.

00:30:17.040 --> 00:30:20.590 align:middle line:84%
They used occult means,
like voodoo dolls and things

00:30:20.590 --> 00:30:22.570 align:middle line:84%
like that, to try
and attack them.

00:30:22.570 --> 00:30:24.550 align:middle line:84%
But the main thing
that they did was

00:30:24.550 --> 00:30:26.890 align:middle line:84%
try to slander their
public reputations,

00:30:26.890 --> 00:30:29.890 align:middle line:84%
by creating propaganda
to say that Dee

00:30:29.890 --> 00:30:31.900 align:middle line:84%
was a black magician
and a sorcerer

00:30:31.900 --> 00:30:36.970 align:middle line:84%
and Elizabeth was part of--
the Antichrist and all of this.

00:30:36.970 --> 00:30:39.280 align:middle line:90%
And that a woman--

00:30:39.280 --> 00:30:41.794 align:middle line:84%
or Elizabeth, a woman, and
specifically Elizabeth,

00:30:41.794 --> 00:30:43.210 align:middle line:84%
being on the throne
of England was

00:30:43.210 --> 00:30:44.560 align:middle line:90%
a sign of the end of the world.

00:30:44.560 --> 00:30:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And they really
wanted to stir up

00:30:46.090 --> 00:30:52.750 align:middle line:84%
the public against the
current ruling powers.

00:30:52.750 --> 00:30:57.000 align:middle line:84%
So it was an ongoing,
kind of gutter level war

00:30:57.000 --> 00:30:59.519 align:middle line:84%
that those two guys waged
against Dee and Elizabeth.

00:30:59.519 --> 00:31:01.060 align:middle line:84%
And it's one that
frankly Dee was not

00:31:01.060 --> 00:31:03.040 align:middle line:84%
particularly prepared
for because he

00:31:03.040 --> 00:31:04.180 align:middle line:90%
was an innocent in a way.

00:31:04.180 --> 00:31:07.720 align:middle line:84%
He was a pure and very noble
seeker after knowledge.

00:31:07.720 --> 00:31:12.160 align:middle line:84%
And he just was not prepared
for people to fight that dirty.

00:31:12.160 --> 00:31:15.370 align:middle line:84%
So he suffered from
their propaganda attacks.

00:31:15.370 --> 00:31:17.770 align:middle line:84%
His reputation
suffers to this day,

00:31:17.770 --> 00:31:19.450 align:middle line:84%
not just from their
propaganda attacks,

00:31:19.450 --> 00:31:24.700 align:middle line:84%
but by many other people,
including James I's regime,

00:31:24.700 --> 00:31:26.890 align:middle line:84%
which came in after
Elizabeth decided to sweep

00:31:26.890 --> 00:31:30.100 align:middle line:90%
all magic under the carpet.

00:31:30.100 --> 00:31:32.920 align:middle line:84%
And so Dee's reputation
has been sullied.

00:31:32.920 --> 00:31:35.080 align:middle line:84%
He was been called a black
magician and a sorcerer

00:31:35.080 --> 00:31:37.660 align:middle line:84%
when he was the
complete opposite.

00:31:37.660 --> 00:31:40.120 align:middle line:84%
And that's something that I've
tried to repair with this.

00:31:40.120 --> 00:31:41.130 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, clearly.

00:31:41.130 --> 00:31:42.910 align:middle line:84%
And you're doing a
beautiful job of it.

00:31:42.910 --> 00:31:43.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Thank you.

00:31:43.210 --> 00:31:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I mean,
and too, in that day,

00:31:44.330 --> 00:31:46.040 align:middle line:90%
there was no defense against it.

00:31:46.040 --> 00:31:47.800 align:middle line:84%
I mean there was
no, like, litigation

00:31:47.800 --> 00:31:48.912 align:middle line:90%
over slander in the day.

00:31:48.912 --> 00:31:50.120 align:middle line:90%
You just had to live with it.

00:31:50.120 --> 00:31:51.495 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Go against
the dark arts.

00:31:51.495 --> 00:31:52.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There was none.

00:31:52.610 --> 00:31:55.450 align:middle line:10%
And so I think
when we're talking

00:31:55.450 --> 00:31:57.080 align:middle line:10%
about these kind of
nuanced characters,

00:31:57.080 --> 00:31:59.110 align:middle line:10%
this is a good time
to bring in Edward

00:31:59.110 --> 00:32:02.590 align:middle line:10%
Kelley and his association
with Edward Kelley

00:32:02.590 --> 00:32:04.280 align:middle line:10%
and what they produced together.

00:32:04.280 --> 00:32:05.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:32:05.080 --> 00:32:07.810 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Because,
again, Edward was

00:32:07.810 --> 00:32:10.630 align:middle line:90%
a mixed bag of human traits.

00:32:10.630 --> 00:32:14.140 align:middle line:84%
And I just want to say
this too, a lot of people

00:32:14.140 --> 00:32:16.210 align:middle line:84%
really enjoyed the
work in the 1960s,

00:32:16.210 --> 00:32:19.170 align:middle line:90%
'70s, of Ruth Montgomery.

00:32:19.170 --> 00:32:21.760 align:middle line:84%
And her association and
her channeled source

00:32:21.760 --> 00:32:22.930 align:middle line:90%
was Arthur Ford.

00:32:22.930 --> 00:32:26.240 align:middle line:84%
Arthur Ford, who had a major
problem with alcohol and such,

00:32:26.240 --> 00:32:28.300 align:middle line:84%
even when he was a
medium in his day.

00:32:28.300 --> 00:32:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And I bring this
up because there

00:32:31.060 --> 00:32:33.850 align:middle line:84%
is a kind of, if you look at
it from a metaphysical point

00:32:33.850 --> 00:32:36.700 align:middle line:84%
of view, a type of
porosity that happens

00:32:36.700 --> 00:32:38.630 align:middle line:84%
within the auric
field, so to speak,

00:32:38.630 --> 00:32:43.030 align:middle line:84%
of people who have addictions,
that allows for a permeability,

00:32:43.030 --> 00:32:46.300 align:middle line:84%
that really other
beings can see through,

00:32:46.300 --> 00:32:48.580 align:middle line:84%
come in through very
easily compared to someone

00:32:48.580 --> 00:32:50.320 align:middle line:90%
who is super-healthy.

00:32:50.320 --> 00:32:52.120 align:middle line:90%
And they're in their zone.

00:32:52.120 --> 00:32:53.080 align:middle line:90%
It's a different deal.

00:32:53.080 --> 00:32:54.106 align:middle line:90%
That's not so permeable.

00:32:54.106 --> 00:32:55.480 align:middle line:84%
And I bring it up
because I think

00:32:55.480 --> 00:32:56.688 align:middle line:90%
it's important to understand.

00:32:56.688 --> 00:33:00.130 align:middle line:84%
That's why so many psychics,
even the best of them,

00:33:00.130 --> 00:33:03.135 align:middle line:84%
are often very flawed on
a deeply personal level.

00:33:03.135 --> 00:33:04.510 align:middle line:84%
So here we go with
Edward Kelley.

00:33:04.510 --> 00:33:06.051 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: That's a
fascinating-- that's

00:33:06.051 --> 00:33:07.250 align:middle line:90%
