and I've known a lot
of psychics and mediums

00:33:27.520 --> 00:33:28.880 align:middle line:90%
with substance abuse issues.

00:33:28.880 --> 00:33:29.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:33:29.280 --> 00:33:31.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: And so it's
not so black and white.

00:33:31.220 --> 00:33:32.440 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's not
black and white at all.

00:33:32.440 --> 00:33:34.090 align:middle line:84%
So I just bring
that up so we can

00:33:34.090 --> 00:33:37.310 align:middle line:84%
set the stage for yet another
nuanced colorful character--

00:33:37.310 --> 00:33:38.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:33:38.110 --> 00:33:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA:
--counterfeiter and all.

00:33:39.760 --> 00:33:40.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Absolutely.

00:33:40.960 --> 00:33:44.680 align:middle line:84%
So Dee is what we refer
to as a hard head.

00:33:44.680 --> 00:33:47.312 align:middle line:90%
So he was, as I probably--

00:33:47.312 --> 00:33:49.770 align:middle line:84%
you probably get a sense of
him from what I've been saying.

00:33:49.770 --> 00:33:50.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:33:50.200 --> 00:33:51.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: He was
very intellectual.

00:33:51.580 --> 00:33:53.080 align:middle line:90%
He was very academic.

00:33:53.080 --> 00:33:55.790 align:middle line:84%
He was on the payroll
of the government.

00:33:55.790 --> 00:33:57.160 align:middle line:90%
He was hyperrational.

00:33:57.160 --> 00:34:00.310 align:middle line:84%
And so he did not have
any innate psychic talent.

00:34:00.310 --> 00:34:01.150 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't open.

00:34:01.150 --> 00:34:02.210 align:middle line:90%
He wasn't empathic.

00:34:02.210 --> 00:34:04.970 align:middle line:84%
He didn't have an artistic
way of viewing the world.

00:34:04.970 --> 00:34:08.710 align:middle line:84%
And so even though he was
fascinated with the theory

00:34:08.710 --> 00:34:10.060 align:middle line:90%
of magic and he spent--

00:34:10.060 --> 00:34:11.949 align:middle line:84%
all the way up to
the age of 50, he

00:34:11.949 --> 00:34:14.080 align:middle line:84%
spent all of his time
studying all the theory,

00:34:14.080 --> 00:34:16.000 align:middle line:84%
and the text, and
the academic side,

00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:17.980 align:middle line:84%
and all the little
bits and pieces.

00:34:17.980 --> 00:34:22.389 align:middle line:84%
But he, himself, his attempts
to actually make magic work

00:34:22.389 --> 00:34:26.500 align:middle line:84%
were not successful because
he couldn't go into a trance

00:34:26.500 --> 00:34:28.570 align:middle line:90%
and go into altered states.

00:34:28.570 --> 00:34:31.150 align:middle line:84%
And so what that meant was
he had to employ people

00:34:31.150 --> 00:34:33.130 align:middle line:90%
to do it with him.

00:34:33.130 --> 00:34:34.929 align:middle line:90%
He had to employ psychics.

00:34:34.929 --> 00:34:37.510 align:middle line:84%
So that he would basically
do a magical ritual to,

00:34:37.510 --> 00:34:39.610 align:middle line:90%
let's say, talk to an angel.

00:34:39.610 --> 00:34:42.219 align:middle line:84%
And then the psychic would
have the vision of the angel,

00:34:42.219 --> 00:34:43.330 align:middle line:90%
instead of him.

00:34:43.330 --> 00:34:45.590 align:middle line:84%
And he would write down
what the psychic saw.

00:34:45.590 --> 00:34:48.100 align:middle line:84%
So that's a working partnership
that's very common in magic.

00:34:48.100 --> 00:34:48.190 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, it is.

00:34:48.190 --> 00:34:49.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: They do it all the time.

00:34:49.090 --> 00:34:51.673 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Edgar Casey, and his
wife, and a lot of people, yes.

00:34:51.673 --> 00:34:53.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: OK.

00:34:53.560 --> 00:34:57.520 align:middle line:84%
So Dee had auditioned
several scryers.

00:34:57.520 --> 00:34:59.050 align:middle line:84%
A scryer is a type
of psychic that

00:34:59.050 --> 00:35:01.450 align:middle line:84%
uses a piece of crystal
or a crystal ball

00:35:01.450 --> 00:35:04.000 align:middle line:84%
as a focus to go
into a trance state.

00:35:04.000 --> 00:35:05.800 align:middle line:84%
And he had auditioned
several of them--

00:35:05.800 --> 00:35:09.310 align:middle line:84%
it was a very common role
in England at this time--

00:35:09.310 --> 00:35:11.627 align:middle line:90%
to kind of middling success.

00:35:11.627 --> 00:35:13.960 align:middle line:84%
But that changed when he met
this fascinating character,

00:35:13.960 --> 00:35:18.520 align:middle line:84%
Edward Kelley, who was
found for him by a talent

00:35:18.520 --> 00:35:21.900 align:middle line:84%
scout for psychics that
the crown had appointed.

00:35:21.900 --> 00:35:24.480 align:middle line:84%
Interesting job titles, it
was the Elizabethan age.

00:35:24.480 --> 00:35:29.190 align:middle line:84%
And Edward Kelley, he brings
a long shadow with him.

00:35:29.190 --> 00:35:30.845 align:middle line:84%
He was half Dee's
age when they met.

00:35:30.845 --> 00:35:37.360 align:middle line:84%
So he was 25 or 26, very
overweight, an alcoholic.

00:35:37.360 --> 00:35:40.620 align:middle line:84%
He had his ears cut off for
being caught forging coins.

00:35:40.620 --> 00:35:43.590 align:middle line:84%
He had been accused of
necromancy and summoning

00:35:43.590 --> 00:35:46.400 align:middle line:84%
corpses out of graves, some of
which is probably exaggerated.

00:35:46.400 --> 00:35:48.270 align:middle line:90%
And some of which may be true.

00:35:48.270 --> 00:35:50.000 align:middle line:90%
And he kind of--

00:35:50.000 --> 00:35:53.250 align:middle line:84%
Dee's writes in his diary that
the day that Kelley showed up

00:35:53.250 --> 00:35:55.080 align:middle line:84%
at Mortlake, which
was Dee's household,

00:35:55.080 --> 00:35:56.190 align:middle line:90%
the moon turned blood red.

00:35:56.190 --> 00:35:59.040 align:middle line:84%
It's like a hammer horror
movie or something.

00:35:59.040 --> 00:36:04.350 align:middle line:84%
But despite his air of
disrespectability and being

00:36:04.350 --> 00:36:06.930 align:middle line:84%
from the wrong side of the
tracks, he could do it.

00:36:06.930 --> 00:36:08.080 align:middle line:90%
He had real psychic--

00:36:08.080 --> 00:36:08.880 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Talent.

00:36:08.880 --> 00:36:10.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: --talent, or
whatever it is, ability

00:36:10.980 --> 00:36:13.860 align:middle line:84%
to go into trances or
just creative imagination,

00:36:13.860 --> 00:36:15.870 align:middle line:90%
whatever it happened to be.

00:36:15.870 --> 00:36:19.260 align:middle line:84%
And Dee was so impressed
with his abilities

00:36:19.260 --> 00:36:21.390 align:middle line:84%
that he put him on payroll
for the next seven years

00:36:21.390 --> 00:36:24.690 align:middle line:84%
and had him do
essentially channeling

00:36:24.690 --> 00:36:27.060 align:middle line:84%
or psychic mediumship,
three times a day,

00:36:27.060 --> 00:36:29.820 align:middle line:84%
for the next seven years, which
was very, very hard on Kelley

00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:31.122 align:middle line:90%
and really wore him down.

00:36:31.122 --> 00:36:32.580 align:middle line:84%
It's also possible
that he may have

00:36:32.580 --> 00:36:36.030 align:middle line:84%
been using some type of
substance to facilitate that.

00:36:36.030 --> 00:36:38.490 align:middle line:84%
And keeping that type
of schedule, using--

00:36:38.490 --> 00:36:40.500 align:middle line:84%
for that long a period,
using whatever substance

00:36:40.500 --> 00:36:44.070 align:middle line:84%
it happened to be,
whatever it was,

00:36:44.070 --> 00:36:46.310 align:middle line:84%
can certainly have
a toll on somebody.

00:36:46.310 --> 00:36:48.580 align:middle line:90%
So he was very erratic.

00:36:48.580 --> 00:36:50.880 align:middle line:84%
He had his ups and downs
while in Dee's employ.

00:36:50.880 --> 00:36:53.430 align:middle line:84%
They formed a incredible
working partnership.

00:36:53.430 --> 00:36:56.130 align:middle line:84%
And they generated over a
thousand pages of records,

00:36:56.130 --> 00:36:58.770 align:middle line:84%
of scrying angels, and speaking
to various spiritual beings,

00:36:58.770 --> 00:37:00.480 align:middle line:84%
which are beautiful
and profound,

00:37:00.480 --> 00:37:03.300 align:middle line:84%
and on par or
greater in language

00:37:03.300 --> 00:37:06.900 align:middle line:84%
than perhaps even the King
James Bible, parts of them.

00:37:06.900 --> 00:37:11.790 align:middle line:84%
And incredible, even just
as a literary record.

00:37:11.790 --> 00:37:15.240 align:middle line:84%
But there were certainly parts
where Kelley became unhinged.

00:37:15.240 --> 00:37:18.910 align:middle line:84%
And it was a tumultuous
working relationship,

00:37:18.910 --> 00:37:20.640 align:middle line:84%
but a fascinating
one at a human level

00:37:20.640 --> 00:37:22.680 align:middle line:84%
between two very
different individuals, who

00:37:22.680 --> 00:37:24.175 align:middle line:90%
formed a greater whole.

00:37:24.175 --> 00:37:25.800 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's
why I brought up

00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:29.460 align:middle line:84%
the difficulty of being
open to other forces.

00:37:29.460 --> 00:37:33.690 align:middle line:84%
Because at the same time, kind
of monstrous types of entities

00:37:33.690 --> 00:37:36.630 align:middle line:84%
started manifesting for
Dee and such as well.

00:37:36.630 --> 00:37:40.080 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like these were
kind of angelic things, kind

00:37:40.080 --> 00:37:43.800 align:middle line:84%
of mixed in with the hodgepodge
of some lower realm creatures.

00:37:43.800 --> 00:37:46.290 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: So as the sessions
went on, at the beginning

00:37:46.290 --> 00:37:49.090 align:middle line:90%
of the sessions, what--

00:37:49.090 --> 00:37:51.540 align:middle line:84%
so first of all, the
point of the sessions

00:37:51.540 --> 00:37:52.914 align:middle line:90%
was for Dee to talk to angels.

00:37:52.914 --> 00:37:53.830 align:middle line:90%
That's what he wanted.

00:37:53.830 --> 00:37:55.680 align:middle line:84%
He wanted to communicate
with angels because, you

00:37:55.680 --> 00:37:57.180 align:middle line:84%
have to remember,
this is perhaps

00:37:57.180 --> 00:38:00.150 align:middle line:90%
the smartest person of his age.

00:38:00.150 --> 00:38:01.260 align:middle line:90%
He'd been all over Europe.

00:38:01.260 --> 00:38:03.480 align:middle line:84%
He'd studied under all the
great intellectual masters

00:38:03.480 --> 00:38:06.160 align:middle line:90%
of the European universities.

00:38:06.160 --> 00:38:07.920 align:middle line:84%
He was smarter,
basically, probably

00:38:07.920 --> 00:38:09.310 align:middle line:90%
than anyone in England.

00:38:09.310 --> 00:38:11.760 align:middle line:84%
He had five times the books
of Oxford and Cambridge,

00:38:11.760 --> 00:38:14.160 align:middle line:84%
each of which had maybe
400, 500 books each.

00:38:14.160 --> 00:38:17.862 align:middle line:84%
He had 2,500 books, maybe
4,000 at one point at Mortlake,

00:38:17.862 --> 00:38:19.320 align:middle line:84%
which is probably
why he was always

00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:20.640 align:middle line:84%
broke because he's spending
all his money on books--

00:38:20.640 --> 00:38:21.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: On books.

00:38:21.440 --> 00:38:23.940 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: --which some of
us can empathize with.

00:38:23.940 --> 00:38:26.430 align:middle line:84%
But he got to a point
where he realized

00:38:26.430 --> 00:38:28.980 align:middle line:84%
if he wanted to know anything
more, he was going to have to,

00:38:28.980 --> 00:38:30.930 align:middle line:84%
in his mind, speak to
higher authorities.

00:38:30.930 --> 00:38:33.430 align:middle line:84%
He couldn't learn anything
more from human beings.

00:38:33.430 --> 00:38:35.700 align:middle line:84%
And so his goal was
to speak to the angels

00:38:35.700 --> 00:38:38.820 align:middle line:84%
and make contact with them, to
recover the original knowledge

00:38:38.820 --> 00:38:39.750 align:middle line:90%
of humanity.

00:38:39.750 --> 00:38:40.710 align:middle line:90%
That was his goal.

00:38:40.710 --> 00:38:44.400 align:middle line:84%
It was totally pure,
totally spiritual.

00:38:44.400 --> 00:38:46.890 align:middle line:84%
But he became involved with
these different scryers

00:38:46.890 --> 00:38:49.020 align:middle line:90%
in order to do that.

00:38:49.020 --> 00:38:52.330 align:middle line:84%
Throughout the sessions, which
lasted about seven years,

00:38:52.330 --> 00:38:53.680 align:middle line:90%
it was a real process.

00:38:53.680 --> 00:38:55.300 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't cut and dry.

00:38:55.300 --> 00:39:00.120 align:middle line:84%
What was happening was Dee and
Kelley were being tuned up.

00:39:00.120 --> 00:39:02.130 align:middle line:84%
The view of the angels,
when they manifested,

00:39:02.130 --> 00:39:04.980 align:middle line:84%
was we're going to
give you knowledge.

00:39:04.980 --> 00:39:07.080 align:middle line:84%
But before you're
worthy to receive it,

00:39:07.080 --> 00:39:08.430 align:middle line:90%
you have to be purified.

00:39:08.430 --> 00:39:10.380 align:middle line:90%
You have to be humbled.

00:39:10.380 --> 00:39:11.340 align:middle line:90%
You have to be--

00:39:11.340 --> 00:39:14.070 align:middle line:84%
all the defilements
of your souls

00:39:14.070 --> 00:39:16.950 align:middle line:90%
must be filed off or removed.

00:39:16.950 --> 00:39:19.230 align:middle line:84%
Because you can't just
receive higher knowledge.

00:39:19.230 --> 00:39:21.570 align:middle line:90%
You have to be prepared.

00:39:21.570 --> 00:39:24.750 align:middle line:90%
Even the Bible says this, right.

00:39:24.750 --> 00:39:27.240 align:middle line:84%
So many years went by,
where Dee and Kelley

00:39:27.240 --> 00:39:31.350 align:middle line:84%
were being tested, purified,
put through various intense

00:39:31.350 --> 00:39:34.770 align:middle line:84%
situations that brought
them always to greater

00:39:34.770 --> 00:39:39.120 align:middle line:90%
levels of faith and humility.

00:39:39.120 --> 00:39:41.760 align:middle line:84%
And in the beginning,
they were being confronted

00:39:41.760 --> 00:39:44.824 align:middle line:90%
by many demonic appearances.

00:39:44.824 --> 00:39:46.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they couldn't
yet tell the difference

00:39:46.740 --> 00:39:48.060 align:middle line:90%
between demons and angels.

00:39:48.060 --> 00:39:49.860 align:middle line:90%
But the angels showed them how.

00:39:49.860 --> 00:39:51.540 align:middle line:84%
And part of the
original sessions

00:39:51.540 --> 00:39:55.590 align:middle line:84%
were, in a sense, an exorcism,
where the angels were kicking

00:39:55.590 --> 00:40:00.660 align:middle line:84%
out all the lower forces
that they saw attached to,

00:40:00.660 --> 00:40:03.600 align:middle line:84%
not just Dee and Kelley,
but all humanity.

00:40:03.600 --> 00:40:05.700 align:middle line:84%
And Kelley himself
had spent a lot

00:40:05.700 --> 00:40:10.650 align:middle line:84%
of time doing demonic types
of magic for personal gain.

00:40:10.650 --> 00:40:12.480 align:middle line:90%
And they picked up on that.

00:40:12.480 --> 00:40:14.130 align:middle line:84%
And so most of
the early sessions

00:40:14.130 --> 00:40:17.220 align:middle line:84%
were the angels kind of pushing
Kelley around and trying

00:40:17.220 --> 00:40:19.510 align:middle line:84%
to get him shaped up, so
that he was spiritually pure

00:40:19.510 --> 00:40:22.014 align:middle line:90%
enough to receive higher wisdom.

00:40:22.014 --> 00:40:23.680 align:middle line:84%
And they have their
work cut out for him

00:40:23.680 --> 00:40:26.560 align:middle line:84%
because he was a
rough character.

00:40:26.560 --> 00:40:28.930 align:middle line:84%
But as the sessions
went on, once they

00:40:28.930 --> 00:40:32.410 align:middle line:84%
got through that period, then
it became almost purely angelic.

00:40:32.410 --> 00:40:35.260 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And what was
the direction and nature

00:40:35.260 --> 00:40:38.230 align:middle line:90%
of the body of work, in summary?

00:40:38.230 --> 00:40:42.400 align:middle line:84%
And then I do want to
get into the end times

00:40:42.400 --> 00:40:46.480 align:middle line:84%
scenario, the mission to
save the 144,000 souls,

00:40:46.480 --> 00:40:47.950 align:middle line:90%
and who those actually were.

00:40:47.950 --> 00:40:50.580 align:middle line:84%
So we'll lead from one
question to the next.

00:40:50.580 --> 00:40:51.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:40:51.640 --> 00:40:54.310 align:middle line:84%
So when the angels
appeared, which

00:40:54.310 --> 00:40:57.760 align:middle line:84%
was pretty quickly
after Kelley showed up,

00:40:57.760 --> 00:41:00.676 align:middle line:84%
the first thing that they did,
after putting Dee and Kelley

00:41:00.676 --> 00:41:02.050 align:middle line:84%
through their
paces, is give them

00:41:02.050 --> 00:41:05.440 align:middle line:84%
a system for making deeper
contact, which is now referred

00:41:05.440 --> 00:41:07.112 align:middle line:84%
to as Enochian
magic, which is not

00:41:07.112 --> 00:41:08.320 align:middle line:90%
a term they used at the time.

00:41:08.320 --> 00:41:10.877 align:middle line:90%
It's a term later writers used.

00:41:10.877 --> 00:41:12.460 align:middle line:84%
And the Enochian
system, and language,

00:41:12.460 --> 00:41:15.970 align:middle line:84%
which was supposed to be the
language that the angels spoke

00:41:15.970 --> 00:41:19.540 align:middle line:84%
before the fall
of-- from Eden, was

00:41:19.540 --> 00:41:21.880 align:middle line:84%
to tune them up and
allow them deeper access

00:41:21.880 --> 00:41:24.010 align:middle line:90%
to the angelic realms.

00:41:24.010 --> 00:41:25.690 align:middle line:84%
Once they got through
that, the angels

00:41:25.690 --> 00:41:28.000 align:middle line:84%
made their agenda
pretty clear, which

00:41:28.000 --> 00:41:31.180 align:middle line:84%
is not different at all from
really what is in the Bible.

00:41:31.180 --> 00:41:33.970 align:middle line:84%
It was that humanity
needs to be redeemed.

00:41:33.970 --> 00:41:35.872 align:middle line:84%
They were not pleased
with the Reformation.

00:41:35.872 --> 00:41:38.080 align:middle line:84%
They weren't pleased with
the Catholic Church either.

00:41:38.080 --> 00:41:39.663 align:middle line:84%
They thought that
humanity had entered

00:41:39.663 --> 00:41:42.700 align:middle line:84%
a very debased and violent
period of history, had fallen

00:41:42.700 --> 00:41:45.670 align:middle line:84%
very far from the
original teachings that

00:41:45.670 --> 00:41:48.470 align:middle line:84%
are either from the Old
Testament or from Christ.

00:41:48.470 --> 00:41:50.210 align:middle line:90%
It's hard to argue with.

00:41:50.210 --> 00:41:53.590 align:middle line:84%
And they wanted to
directly use Dee and Kelley

00:41:53.590 --> 00:41:57.490 align:middle line:84%
as agents to advance their
vision for the world, which

00:41:57.490 --> 00:42:00.500 align:middle line:84%
is kind of intense,
or very intense.

00:42:00.500 --> 00:42:03.370 align:middle line:84%
What the angels wanted
was-- their view was,

00:42:03.370 --> 00:42:06.700 align:middle line:84%
humans have had their
chance to get it right.

00:42:06.700 --> 00:42:07.840 align:middle line:90%
They haven't got it right.

00:42:07.840 --> 00:42:10.210 align:middle line:84%
We would like to
take the wheel now,

00:42:10.210 --> 00:42:13.610 align:middle line:84%
in order to-- what we
want is a new religion.

00:42:13.610 --> 00:42:16.900 align:middle line:84%
It's a new, hermetic-based
super-religion,

00:42:16.900 --> 00:42:21.070 align:middle line:84%
combining Catholicism,
Protestantism, Judaism, Islam,

00:42:21.070 --> 00:42:21.880 align:middle line:90%
paganism even.

00:42:21.880 --> 00:42:23.296 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And very
hermetic, yeah.

00:42:23.296 --> 00:42:24.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Very hermetic.

00:42:24.310 --> 00:42:26.500 align:middle line:84%
One universal religion
of love, which

00:42:26.500 --> 00:42:28.630 align:middle line:84%
will be ministered by
the angels directly.

00:42:28.630 --> 00:42:32.560 align:middle line:84%
They wanted humans to have a
way to contact the divine realms

00:42:32.560 --> 00:42:34.540 align:middle line:84%
one on one, instead
of having to deal

00:42:34.540 --> 00:42:35.729 align:middle line:90%
with a corrupt institution.

00:42:35.729 --> 00:42:37.270 align:middle line:84%
Although they also
thought the people

00:42:37.270 --> 00:42:40.010 align:middle line:84%
should still be attached
to the body of the Church,

00:42:40.010 --> 00:42:42.700 align:middle line:84%
because it was an
important tool.

00:42:42.700 --> 00:42:45.880 align:middle line:84%
And communion was important,
and all of these things.

00:42:45.880 --> 00:42:51.100 align:middle line:84%
But they wanted almost
to directly redeem

00:42:51.100 --> 00:42:53.630 align:middle line:84%
humanity, almost
in spite of itself,

00:42:53.630 --> 00:42:55.250 align:middle line:84%
which hasn't worked
out very well.

00:42:55.250 --> 00:42:56.050 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:42:56.050 --> 00:42:57.860 align:middle line:84%
They wanted a kind
of global conversion.

00:42:57.860 --> 00:42:58.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yes.

00:42:58.660 --> 00:42:59.780 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:42:59.780 --> 00:43:01.446 align:middle line:84%
So they had their
work cut out for them,

00:43:01.446 --> 00:43:03.750 align:middle line:84%
proselytizing and
trying to get buy-ins

00:43:03.750 --> 00:43:05.710 align:middle line:84%
in other countries,
leadership, churches,

00:43:05.710 --> 00:43:08.585 align:middle line:90%
and so forth, not easy.

00:43:08.585 --> 00:43:10.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Their original plan
was they wanted-- in addition

00:43:10.960 --> 00:43:14.020 align:middle line:84%
to this, they wanted one
world empire, under Elizabeth

00:43:14.020 --> 00:43:16.180 align:middle line:84%
as the sovereign,
which Dee already

00:43:16.180 --> 00:43:18.615 align:middle line:90%
laid the groundwork for.

00:43:18.615 --> 00:43:19.990 align:middle line:84%
So when you step
back and you see

00:43:19.990 --> 00:43:22.270 align:middle line:84%
that Dee is responsible
not only for creating

00:43:22.270 --> 00:43:24.830 align:middle line:84%
the British empire, which
ruled most of the planet,

00:43:24.830 --> 00:43:27.607 align:middle line:84%
but also potentially--
the plan was

00:43:27.607 --> 00:43:29.440 align:middle line:84%
to create one religion
that ruled everybody.

00:43:29.440 --> 00:43:31.550 align:middle line:90%
That's a big plan.

00:43:31.550 --> 00:43:32.762 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:43:32.762 --> 00:43:34.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: In a way,
it has come true.

00:43:34.220 --> 00:43:36.886 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think that the British
empire, if you really step back

00:43:36.886 --> 00:43:38.350 align:middle line:84%
and you look at
the British empire,

00:43:38.350 --> 00:43:40.272 align:middle line:84%
or in some ways the
American empire,

00:43:40.272 --> 00:43:41.980 align:middle line:84%
you can definitely
see that parts of that

00:43:41.980 --> 00:43:44.727 align:middle line:90%
have perhaps influenced people.

00:43:44.727 --> 00:43:45.550 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Uh-huh.

00:43:45.550 --> 00:43:47.417 align:middle line:90%
Let's get into--

00:43:47.417 --> 00:43:49.000 align:middle line:84%
I think we can just
kind of skip over.

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:51.760 align:middle line:84%
There's one part I wanted to
get into, about Kelley's life.

00:43:51.760 --> 00:43:54.400 align:middle line:84%
Because of the lack of
funding and the constant need

00:43:54.400 --> 00:43:58.960 align:middle line:84%
for patronage, he tended to
flip allegiances, to work for,

00:43:58.960 --> 00:44:01.810 align:middle line:84%
whether it's Protestant,
Catholic, or whatnot, kind

00:44:01.810 --> 00:44:02.980 align:middle line:90%
of anybody.

00:44:02.980 --> 00:44:04.750 align:middle line:84%
In a sense, so that
he could get the funds

00:44:04.750 --> 00:44:06.250 align:middle line:90%
needed to do his real work.

00:44:06.250 --> 00:44:07.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:44:07.050 --> 00:44:10.270 align:middle line:84%
And the crazy thing is the
angels encouraged him in that.

00:44:10.270 --> 00:44:12.586 align:middle line:84%
They kind of said, look,
you're working for us now.

00:44:12.586 --> 00:44:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And you have a
direct connection.

00:44:13.960 --> 00:44:15.397 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry too much about--

00:44:15.397 --> 00:44:17.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This petty
politics of the planet.

00:44:17.230 --> 00:44:17.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:44:17.960 --> 00:44:18.760 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:44:18.760 --> 00:44:21.520 align:middle line:84%
And they were helpful
in steering him.

00:44:21.520 --> 00:44:24.354 align:middle line:84%
There were many times
that the Catholic Church--

00:44:24.354 --> 00:44:26.770 align:middle line:84%
the Jesuits probably would
have killed him multiple times.

00:44:26.770 --> 00:44:29.103 align:middle line:84%
They were trying to bring Dee
and Kelley to the Vatican,

00:44:29.103 --> 00:44:31.930 align:middle line:84%
where they probably would
have been tortured and killed

00:44:31.930 --> 00:44:33.220 align:middle line:90%
for heresy.

00:44:33.220 --> 00:44:37.235 align:middle line:84%
And there are many times where
they narrowly avoided disaster.

00:44:37.235 --> 00:44:39.080 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So they
probably looked after.

00:44:39.080 --> 00:44:39.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:44:39.450 --> 00:44:40.650 align:middle line:90%
It's all there in the records.

00:44:40.650 --> 00:44:41.140 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely.

00:44:41.140 --> 00:44:41.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: It's crazy.

00:44:41.640 --> 00:44:42.440 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK.

00:44:42.440 --> 00:44:46.990 align:middle line:84%
So let's get into the
144,000, the end times

00:44:46.990 --> 00:44:50.770 align:middle line:84%
scenario, 12 tribes of Israel,
new world order, all of that.

00:44:50.770 --> 00:44:53.500 align:middle line:84%
And then start getting
into the implications

00:44:53.500 --> 00:44:55.450 align:middle line:84%
of how that carried
down through history

00:44:55.450 --> 00:44:57.160 align:middle line:84%
and how it's still
playing out today

00:44:57.160 --> 00:44:59.720 align:middle line:84%
because this is really the
crux of it in a lot of ways

00:44:59.720 --> 00:45:00.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: A good question.

00:45:00.720 --> 00:45:00.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:45:00.920 --> 00:45:01.970 align:middle line:90%
And we have time.

00:45:01.970 --> 00:45:02.770 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: OK.

00:45:02.770 --> 00:45:04.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Big answers are good.

00:45:04.310 --> 00:45:06.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: So basically
what the angels

00:45:06.550 --> 00:45:10.780 align:middle line:84%
said is, humanity should
be directly redeemed.

00:45:10.780 --> 00:45:13.450 align:middle line:84%
And what they
thought is the events

00:45:13.450 --> 00:45:17.240 align:middle line:84%
of the Book of Revelation
need to be reenacted.

00:45:17.240 --> 00:45:22.582 align:middle line:84%
And the angels, they wanted a
salvation plan for humanity.

00:45:22.582 --> 00:45:24.790 align:middle line:84%
They thought that it was
already the end of the world

00:45:24.790 --> 00:45:28.570 align:middle line:84%
and humanity was laboring under
the reign of the Antichrist.

00:45:28.570 --> 00:45:32.410 align:middle line:84%
Which, it's interesting to think
about because we often look

00:45:32.410 --> 00:45:33.787 align:middle line:90%
at these things as literal.

00:45:33.787 --> 00:45:36.370 align:middle line:84%
Like somebody is always coming
out saying the end of the world

00:45:36.370 --> 00:45:37.940 align:middle line:90%
is next Thursday.

00:45:37.940 --> 00:45:41.330 align:middle line:84%
But if you really
step back again.

00:45:41.330 --> 00:45:44.380 align:middle line:84%
And I think that divine events,
whatever, these things probably

00:45:44.380 --> 00:45:47.290 align:middle line:84%
play out on long
timelines, even if you just

00:45:47.290 --> 00:45:50.410 align:middle line:90%
look at them as metaphorical.

00:45:50.410 --> 00:45:54.800 align:middle line:84%
The Elizabethan era was, what,
400 years ago, 500 years ago.

00:45:54.800 --> 00:45:56.800 align:middle line:84%
If you think about how
much things have crumbled

00:45:56.800 --> 00:45:59.050 align:middle line:84%
since then, the degradation
of the environment,

00:45:59.050 --> 00:46:00.750 align:middle line:84%
the pollution of
the planet, it's

00:46:00.750 --> 00:46:02.833 align:middle line:84%
hard to argue that things
aren't at least a little

00:46:02.833 --> 00:46:03.880 align:middle line:90%
bit apocalyptic.

00:46:03.880 --> 00:46:07.420 align:middle line:84%
So Dee was convinced that the
angels meant-- the angels told

00:46:07.420 --> 00:46:08.890 align:middle line:90%
him the world would end in '88.

00:46:08.890 --> 00:46:11.050 align:middle line:90%
And he thought this meant 1588.

00:46:11.050 --> 00:46:14.407 align:middle line:84%
But it seems they
meant something else.

00:46:14.407 --> 00:46:16.240 align:middle line:84%
They never said it would
be a specific date.

00:46:16.240 --> 00:46:19.360 align:middle line:84%
It seems that for
beings like that,

00:46:19.360 --> 00:46:23.590 align:middle line:84%
they probably see on
very long time-frames.

00:46:23.590 --> 00:46:28.210 align:middle line:84%
But what they wanted
was to prepare the way

00:46:28.210 --> 00:46:30.550 align:middle line:90%
for the salvation of humanity.

00:46:30.550 --> 00:46:33.070 align:middle line:84%
And their way of doing
that was this idea

00:46:33.070 --> 00:46:35.255 align:middle line:90%
of a new religion and a new--

00:46:35.255 --> 00:46:37.130 align:middle line:84%
the spread of Christianity
around the planet,

00:46:37.130 --> 00:46:39.776 align:middle line:84%
which is what happened, thanks
to the British empire-- or not,

00:46:39.776 --> 00:46:41.650 align:middle line:84%
no thanks, depending on
what your on that is.

00:46:41.650 --> 00:46:42.170 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:46:42.170 --> 00:46:42.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: And a lot
of peopled suffered.

00:46:42.770 --> 00:46:45.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Imperialism has an
up and downside, for sure.

00:46:45.100 --> 00:46:46.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: A lot of
people suffered.

00:46:46.030 --> 00:46:46.920 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes, a lot.

00:46:46.920 --> 00:46:50.080 align:middle line:90%


00:46:50.080 --> 00:46:51.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: So that's
kind of what happened.

00:46:51.790 --> 00:46:54.980 align:middle line:84%
And when the British empire
spread around the planet,

00:46:54.980 --> 00:46:56.440 align:middle line:90%
it was with that mythology.

00:46:56.440 --> 00:46:59.060 align:middle line:84%
Whether that comes from
Dee directly is arguable.

00:46:59.060 --> 00:47:01.060 align:middle line:84%
But he certainly
had an influence.

00:47:01.060 --> 00:47:03.580 align:middle line:84%
And the ideology of
the British Empire

00:47:03.580 --> 00:47:06.490 align:middle line:84%
was spreading Christianity,
and thereby civilization,

00:47:06.490 --> 00:47:07.660 align:middle line:90%
around the planet.

00:47:07.660 --> 00:47:11.650 align:middle line:84%
And thereby saving people,
even at sword point.

00:47:11.650 --> 00:47:15.100 align:middle line:84%
When global power transferred
to the American empire

00:47:15.100 --> 00:47:17.920 align:middle line:84%
after the British empire
fell around World War I,

00:47:17.920 --> 00:47:19.870 align:middle line:90%
the story was the same.

00:47:19.870 --> 00:47:22.660 align:middle line:84%
America, particularly if you
look at the evangelical right

00:47:22.660 --> 00:47:24.130 align:middle line:90%
in America.

00:47:24.130 --> 00:47:26.849 align:middle line:84%
There was a PEW
Forum study in 2006

00:47:26.849 --> 00:47:28.390 align:middle line:84%
that said that one
in three Americans

00:47:28.390 --> 00:47:32.650 align:middle line:84%
believes that Jesus will
return in our lifetimes.

00:47:32.650 --> 00:47:35.290 align:middle line:84%
And it's far from
being a fringe belief.

00:47:35.290 --> 00:47:37.932 align:middle line:84%
It's, in fact, probably the
dominant belief in America.

00:47:37.932 --> 00:47:39.640 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: If you drive
across the country

00:47:39.640 --> 00:47:42.490 align:middle line:84%
and listen to the only stations
that have any wattage, which

00:47:42.490 --> 00:47:45.370 align:middle line:84%
are Christian radio stations,
fundamentalist Christian radio

00:47:45.370 --> 00:47:48.880 align:middle line:84%
stations, you hear the talk a
lot as you're driving along.

00:47:48.880 --> 00:47:52.060 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's kind of shocking if
you're not part of that group.

00:47:52.060 --> 00:47:52.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Right.

00:47:52.860 --> 00:47:53.660 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:47:53.660 --> 00:47:56.890 align:middle line:84%
And you look at things
like the success

00:47:56.890 --> 00:47:58.384 align:middle line:84%
of the Left Behind
books, which are

00:47:58.384 --> 00:47:59.800 align:middle line:84%
the most popular
books in America,

00:47:59.800 --> 00:48:02.860 align:middle line:84%
I think outside of the Bible,
more than Stephen King.

00:48:02.860 --> 00:48:08.170 align:middle line:84%
So literalism, fundamentalist
literalism, it's a big--

00:48:08.170 --> 00:48:11.270 align:middle line:90%
and it's not just the public.

00:48:11.270 --> 00:48:14.590 align:middle line:84%
It's also, I think, that
apocalyptic literalism

00:48:14.590 --> 00:48:17.710 align:middle line:84%
has been a driving force
in both British and then

00:48:17.710 --> 00:48:18.580 align:middle line:90%
American politics.

00:48:18.580 --> 00:48:19.510 align:middle line:84%
Absolutely in American politics
for the last 100 years.

00:48:19.510 --> 00:48:20.885 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's
what I was going

00:48:20.885 --> 00:48:23.800 align:middle line:84%
to ask you because elite power
circles, this really factors

00:48:23.800 --> 00:48:27.670 align:middle line:84%
hugely in, almost like
in the belief it's

00:48:27.670 --> 00:48:30.730 align:middle line:84%
best for all concerned to
hasten the end of times.

00:48:30.730 --> 00:48:31.690 align:middle line:90%
And that's a danger.

00:48:31.690 --> 00:48:32.540 align:middle line:90%
That's dangerous.

00:48:32.540 --> 00:48:34.630 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're
dealing with right now.

00:48:34.630 --> 00:48:35.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:48:35.430 --> 00:48:36.910 align:middle line:90%
I mean you look at--

00:48:36.910 --> 00:48:38.440 align:middle line:84%
during the Reagan
administration,

00:48:38.440 --> 00:48:41.950 align:middle line:84%
Reagan believed that it was
his divinely appointed gift,

00:48:41.950 --> 00:48:43.930 align:middle line:84%
as inspired by Hal
Lindsay, who was

00:48:43.930 --> 00:48:46.180 align:middle line:84%
a famous Christian
writer in the '70s,

00:48:46.180 --> 00:48:47.890 align:middle line:84%
that it was the
end of the world.

00:48:47.890 --> 00:48:52.150 align:middle line:84%
And his divinely appointed
role was to hasten or shepherd

00:48:52.150 --> 00:48:54.490 align:middle line:84%
humanity through the end of
days and the fight with Gog

00:48:54.490 --> 00:48:56.720 align:middle line:90%
and Magog, which was Russia.

00:48:56.720 --> 00:49:03.040 align:middle line:84%
And that he was God's directly
chosen appointee to do that.

00:49:03.040 --> 00:49:06.670 align:middle line:84%
Now, this seems a
little eccentric

00:49:06.670 --> 00:49:09.220 align:middle line:84%
until you realize that this was
a game that was and is being

00:49:09.220 --> 00:49:11.030 align:middle line:90%
played with nuclear weapons.

00:49:11.030 --> 00:49:11.830 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:49:11.830 --> 00:49:13.246 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: I mean,
this was something

00:49:13.246 --> 00:49:16.340 align:middle line:84%
that was enacted as mutually
assured destruction.

00:49:16.340 --> 00:49:18.490 align:middle line:90%
And during the second Bush--

00:49:18.490 --> 00:49:21.940 align:middle line:84%
or Bush Two, the Bush,
Jr., administration,

00:49:21.940 --> 00:49:24.700 align:middle line:84%
George Bush, also very
influenced by Billy Graham,

00:49:24.700 --> 00:49:28.090 align:middle line:84%
by the evangelicals, believed
that it was his divine mission

00:49:28.090 --> 00:49:30.160 align:middle line:84%
to hasten the
apocalypse by going

00:49:30.160 --> 00:49:31.720 align:middle line:90%
to war in the Middle East.

00:49:31.720 --> 00:49:36.430 align:middle line:84%
He famously attempted to elicit
the support of Jacques Chirac,

00:49:36.430 --> 00:49:40.810 align:middle line:84%
in France, in the war effort,
by telling him that he saw--

00:49:40.810 --> 00:49:43.660 align:middle line:84%
he'd had a vision in prayer
that he'd seen Gog and Magog

00:49:43.660 --> 00:49:45.430 align:middle line:90%
at work in the Middle East.

00:49:45.430 --> 00:49:48.190 align:middle line:84%
This is perhaps
not who we should

00:49:48.190 --> 00:49:51.970 align:middle line:84%
have steering the ship in a 21st
century technological society.

00:49:51.970 --> 00:49:53.140 align:middle line:90%
But it's certainly--

00:49:53.140 --> 00:49:54.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It's still there.

00:49:54.320 --> 00:49:55.635 align:middle line:90%
It's still there.

00:49:55.635 --> 00:49:56.810 align:middle line:90%
It's steering the ship.

00:49:56.810 --> 00:49:59.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: But we need to
understand it because it's--

00:49:59.800 --> 00:50:01.900 align:middle line:84%
to dismiss it, I
think would also

00:50:01.900 --> 00:50:05.020 align:middle line:84%
be a mistake because so
many people believe it.

00:50:05.020 --> 00:50:07.600 align:middle line:90%
And I'm always of the opinion--

00:50:07.600 --> 00:50:12.400 align:middle line:84%
I've long been of the opinion,
as a journalist and a writer,

00:50:12.400 --> 00:50:13.900 align:middle line:84%
if you want to
understand why people

00:50:13.900 --> 00:50:15.730 align:middle line:84%
do the things that
they do, you have

00:50:15.730 --> 00:50:18.196 align:middle line:90%
to look at what they believe.

00:50:18.196 --> 00:50:19.570 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
take it seriously

00:50:19.570 --> 00:50:21.460 align:middle line:84%
at least that they
take it seriously,

00:50:21.460 --> 00:50:23.579 align:middle line:84%
and not be dismissive
or look down at it.

00:50:23.579 --> 00:50:25.120 align:middle line:84%
I think that if we
want to understand

00:50:25.120 --> 00:50:28.655 align:middle line:84%
each other as human beings,
we need to understand

00:50:28.655 --> 00:50:29.530 align:middle line:90%
each other's beliefs.

00:50:29.530 --> 00:50:33.064 align:middle line:84%
You can't understand why
the evangelical right does

00:50:33.064 --> 00:50:34.480 align:middle line:84%
what it does without
understanding

00:50:34.480 --> 00:50:35.688 align:middle line:90%
the script they're following.

00:50:35.688 --> 00:50:38.650 align:middle line:84%
And so I think for that
reason, it's important to--

00:50:38.650 --> 00:50:40.300 align:middle line:84%
for that reason and
many more, I think

00:50:40.300 --> 00:50:42.377 align:middle line:90%
it's important to understand.

00:50:42.377 --> 00:50:43.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I think so, too.

00:50:43.460 --> 00:50:47.530 align:middle line:84%
And I just recently interviewed
an author named Mark Stavish.

00:50:47.530 --> 00:50:50.200 align:middle line:84%
And he had written
about egregores.

00:50:50.200 --> 00:50:52.690 align:middle line:84%
And when you speak about
the notion of an egregore,

00:50:52.690 --> 00:50:57.310 align:middle line:84%
perhaps one of the biggest, most
powerful egregores in existence

00:50:57.310 --> 00:50:59.110 align:middle line:90%
is the end times notion.

00:50:59.110 --> 00:51:00.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:51:00.340 --> 00:51:03.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so that does
have a life of its own

00:51:03.100 --> 00:51:07.000 align:middle line:84%
and does feed back to those
who are in positions of power

00:51:07.000 --> 00:51:08.230 align:middle line:90%
in decision making.

00:51:08.230 --> 00:51:09.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Absolutely, and
it's not just Christianity.

00:51:09.860 --> 00:51:10.660 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: No.

00:51:10.660 --> 00:51:12.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: All of the world
religions have that.

00:51:12.850 --> 00:51:15.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, the
fundamentalist world religions

00:51:15.250 --> 00:51:16.100 align:middle line:90%
in particular, yes.

00:51:16.100 --> 00:51:16.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Yeah.

00:51:16.930 --> 00:51:18.689 align:middle line:90%
And it's interesting.

00:51:18.689 --> 00:51:20.980 align:middle line:84%
You know, I read a lot of
material from people who were

00:51:20.980 --> 00:51:26.041 align:middle line:84%
in Bush, Jr.'s White House and
things like that, and Reagan's.

00:51:26.041 --> 00:51:27.790 align:middle line:84%
And it's not just
Republicans, by the way.

00:51:27.790 --> 00:51:29.030 align:middle line:90%
It's Democrats as well.

00:51:29.030 --> 00:51:29.980 align:middle line:90%
It's on both sides.

00:51:29.980 --> 00:51:31.480 align:middle line:90%
As people get closer to--

00:51:31.480 --> 00:51:35.398 align:middle line:90%


00:51:35.398 --> 00:51:38.350 align:middle line:84%
it's a mythology that's very
appealing to people in power

00:51:38.350 --> 00:51:42.970 align:middle line:84%
because it grants them a sense
of having a special divine

00:51:42.970 --> 00:51:45.310 align:middle line:90%
role to play on the world stage.

00:51:45.310 --> 00:51:48.940 align:middle line:84%
And even people who don't
start out as very evangelical

00:51:48.940 --> 00:51:52.220 align:middle line:84%
become very interested
in that way of thinking,

00:51:52.220 --> 00:51:55.420 align:middle line:90%
which is understandable.

00:51:55.420 --> 00:51:58.984 align:middle line:84%
It's just something that's been
with humanity for a long time.

00:51:58.984 --> 00:52:00.400 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's not
just Christianity.

00:52:00.400 --> 00:52:02.380 align:middle line:84%
It's lots of
different religions.

00:52:02.380 --> 00:52:07.630 align:middle line:84%
My personal view
is yes-- and, we

00:52:07.630 --> 00:52:10.464 align:middle line:84%
should focus on also some
sustainability plans.

00:52:10.464 --> 00:52:12.130 align:middle line:84%
Like, if the world
doesn't end, maybe we

00:52:12.130 --> 00:52:13.220 align:middle line:84%
should make sure of things
are OK during the end times.

00:52:13.220 --> 00:52:13.570 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:52:13.570 --> 00:52:14.770 align:middle line:90%
I'm in your camp.

00:52:14.770 --> 00:52:17.590 align:middle line:84%
Nice to make some
better plans than that.

00:52:17.590 --> 00:52:19.762 align:middle line:84%
So let's get down
to the notion--

00:52:19.762 --> 00:52:21.970 align:middle line:84%
we have about five minutes
left to kind of wrap this.

00:52:21.970 --> 00:52:23.770 align:middle line:90%
Let's get down to the notion.

00:52:23.770 --> 00:52:25.780 align:middle line:84%
These people who are
power elite believe

00:52:25.780 --> 00:52:27.880 align:middle line:84%
that they are among the
ones who will be saved.

00:52:27.880 --> 00:52:32.020 align:middle line:84%
They are always among the
chosen ones, no matter what.

00:52:32.020 --> 00:52:34.360 align:middle line:90%
And so who are the 144,000?

00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:37.310 align:middle line:84%
How was that originally
put out in Dee's day?

00:52:37.310 --> 00:52:39.760 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: So in the
Book of Revelations,

00:52:39.760 --> 00:52:42.280 align:middle line:84%
there's a bit about
the 144,000 that

00:52:42.280 --> 00:52:44.230 align:middle line:84%
will be saved at the
end of the world.

00:52:44.230 --> 00:52:46.660 align:middle line:84%
Elaine Pagels, who's a
fascinating and brilliant

00:52:46.660 --> 00:52:50.410 align:middle line:84%
scholar on gnosticism, has a
very interesting take on this,

00:52:50.410 --> 00:52:52.990 align:middle line:84%
where having examined the
original political context

00:52:52.990 --> 00:52:54.300 align:middle line:90%
of this--

00:52:54.300 --> 00:52:57.100 align:middle line:84%
the evangelical Christians
will not like this.

00:52:57.100 --> 00:53:03.550 align:middle line:84%
The Book of Revelation was
written by John of Patmos

00:53:03.550 --> 00:53:06.235 align:middle line:84%
during the time following
the death of Christ,

00:53:06.235 --> 00:53:08.110 align:middle line:84%
from a very different
perspective of the rest

00:53:08.110 --> 00:53:10.790 align:middle line:90%
of the New Testament.

00:53:10.790 --> 00:53:13.720 align:middle line:84%
The point she makes
very convincingly

00:53:13.720 --> 00:53:15.304 align:middle line:84%
is that following
the death of Christ,

00:53:15.304 --> 00:53:17.053 align:middle line:84%
there were actually
two different factions

00:53:17.053 --> 00:53:17.950 align:middle line:90%
of Christians.

00:53:17.950 --> 00:53:22.736 align:middle line:84%
There were the Jewish converts
to the new religion of-- or it

00:53:22.736 --> 00:53:23.860 align:middle line:90%
wasn't even a new religion.

00:53:23.860 --> 00:53:27.040 align:middle line:84%
There were the Jewish people
who believed that Christ

00:53:27.040 --> 00:53:28.540 align:middle line:90%
was the Jewish messiah.

00:53:28.540 --> 00:53:31.780 align:middle line:84%
And then many who
did not, which is now

00:53:31.780 --> 00:53:33.520 align:middle line:90%
the mainstream view of Judaism,

00:53:33.520 --> 00:53:38.530 align:middle line:84%
There were also--
when Saul of Tarsus

00:53:38.530 --> 00:53:40.480 align:middle line:84%
had his conversion on
the road to Damascus

00:53:40.480 --> 00:53:43.790 align:middle line:84%
and became St. Paul, long
after the death of Christ,

00:53:43.790 --> 00:53:46.510 align:middle line:84%
he said that he was given a
vision that he should open up

00:53:46.510 --> 00:53:48.010 align:middle line:84%
the covenant to all
nations, meaning

00:53:48.010 --> 00:53:51.380 align:middle line:84%
the original covenant between
Moses and the Jewish people.

00:53:51.380 --> 00:53:52.840 align:middle line:90%
And that this was for everyone.

00:53:52.840 --> 00:53:55.010 align:middle line:90%
And that it had to be opened.

00:53:55.010 --> 00:53:57.094 align:middle line:84%
And so he then became the
head of this new thing

00:53:57.094 --> 00:53:58.510 align:middle line:84%
called Christianity,
which has now

00:53:58.510 --> 00:54:01.090 align:middle line:84%
become the most successful
religion in world history.

00:54:01.090 --> 00:54:05.440 align:middle line:84%
But what he did was convert
Greek and Roman pagans,

00:54:05.440 --> 00:54:08.230 align:middle line:84%
and even people from North
Africa, to this new religion.

00:54:08.230 --> 00:54:14.940 align:middle line:84%
This was not-- you can imagine
the Jewish people who followed,

00:54:14.940 --> 00:54:18.085 align:middle line:84%
accepted Christ as the messiah,
being like, hey, wait a minute.

00:54:18.085 --> 00:54:19.600 align:middle line:90%
That's not what this is about.

00:54:19.600 --> 00:54:21.660 align:middle line:84%
Christ was here to fulfill
the covenant with us.

00:54:21.660 --> 00:54:23.502 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't to be
open to all people.

00:54:23.502 --> 00:54:25.210 align:middle line:84%
And so what you have
in the New Testament

00:54:25.210 --> 00:54:30.550 align:middle line:84%
is the Pauline Letters, which
are from the camp following

00:54:30.550 --> 00:54:31.432 align:middle line:90%
St. Paul.

00:54:31.432 --> 00:54:32.890 align:middle line:84%
And then you have
Revelation, which

00:54:32.890 --> 00:54:36.020 align:middle line:84%
was written from the perspective
of the Jewish followers

00:54:36.020 --> 00:54:36.820 align:middle line:90%
of Christ.

00:54:36.820 --> 00:54:39.040 align:middle line:84%
And in the Book of
Revelation, when

00:54:39.040 --> 00:54:41.230 align:middle line:84%
they talk about the
144,000 to be saved,

00:54:41.230 --> 00:54:44.440 align:middle line:84%
what that originally meant was
the Jewish followers of Christ.

00:54:44.440 --> 00:54:46.780 align:middle line:84%
And that everyone else
was not to be saved,

00:54:46.780 --> 00:54:49.780 align:middle line:90%
which is contentious.

00:54:49.780 --> 00:54:51.470 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Contentious,
to say the least.

00:54:51.470 --> 00:54:52.270 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:54:52.270 --> 00:54:53.800 align:middle line:84%
So now, that's been
kind of flipped.

00:54:53.800 --> 00:54:55.540 align:middle line:84%
And if you listen to
the Jehovah Witness,

00:54:55.540 --> 00:54:56.830 align:middle line:84%
then it's a whole
different story again.

00:54:56.830 --> 00:54:57.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Sure.

00:54:57.260 --> 00:54:58.090 align:middle line:90%
Everyone's got their story.

00:54:58.090 --> 00:54:59.380 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Everybody's
their story of the 144,000.

00:54:59.380 --> 00:55:01.000 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Isn't religion fun?

00:55:01.000 --> 00:55:02.900 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Isn't it fun?

00:55:02.900 --> 00:55:05.560 align:middle line:84%
So we have just a couple
minutes left to take it back

00:55:05.560 --> 00:55:08.230 align:middle line:90%
into this kind of larger story.

00:55:08.230 --> 00:55:10.600 align:middle line:90%
How would you wrap this part--

00:55:10.600 --> 00:55:13.060 align:middle line:84%
we literally have two minutes--
wrap this part of the story

00:55:13.060 --> 00:55:15.699 align:middle line:84%
back into John Dee
and his contributions?

00:55:15.699 --> 00:55:17.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: I think that it's
important to understand

00:55:17.740 --> 00:55:20.860 align:middle line:84%
that this time
period-- the ideas

00:55:20.860 --> 00:55:23.710 align:middle line:84%
that were formulated in this
time period are still with us.

00:55:23.710 --> 00:55:26.770 align:middle line:84%
I see John Dee as like
a computer programmer

00:55:26.770 --> 00:55:30.550 align:middle line:84%
who created the computer code
that our society is running on.

00:55:30.550 --> 00:55:33.080 align:middle line:10%
And to understand
that code, and perhaps

00:55:33.080 --> 00:55:35.080 align:middle line:10%
to change it and update
it for the modern world,

00:55:35.080 --> 00:55:37.627 align:middle line:10%
we should understand
where it came from.

00:55:37.627 --> 00:55:38.710 align:middle line:90%
And I particularly think--

00:55:38.710 --> 00:55:40.690 align:middle line:84%
I would particularly
like to underline

00:55:40.690 --> 00:55:45.550 align:middle line:84%
that the apocalyptic idea
is much more dangerous to us

00:55:45.550 --> 00:55:47.834 align:middle line:84%
as a species now that
we have nuclear weapons.

00:55:47.834 --> 00:55:48.750 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I know that.

00:55:48.750 --> 00:55:51.190 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: Now that we have
nanotechnology, biotechnology,

00:55:51.190 --> 00:55:54.280 align:middle line:84%
the ability to kill people
many, many times over,

00:55:54.280 --> 00:55:56.380 align:middle line:84%
everyone, all life,
when we're at the brink

00:55:56.380 --> 00:55:58.540 align:middle line:90%
of ecological collapse.

00:55:58.540 --> 00:55:59.950 align:middle line:90%
So perhaps we need a--

00:55:59.950 --> 00:56:01.444 align:middle line:90%
John Dee created one myth.

00:56:01.444 --> 00:56:02.860 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps we need a
new one that's--

00:56:02.860 --> 00:56:03.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: A counter myth.

00:56:03.230 --> 00:56:05.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: --a bit more
supportive-- yes-- of life.

00:56:05.230 --> 00:56:07.340 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I couldn't agree more.

00:56:07.340 --> 00:56:10.360 align:middle line:84%
And is it-- can we get our hands
on the "Monas Hieroglyphica?"

00:56:10.360 --> 00:56:10.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LOUV: Sure.

00:56:10.690 --> 00:56:10.960 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:56:10.960 --> 00:56:11.918 align:middle line:90%
You can find it online.

00:56:11.918 --> 00:56:13.870 align:middle line:90%
It's freely available as a PDF.

00:56:13.870 --> 00:56:16.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And would you
recommend we all read it?

00:56:16.070 --> 00:56:17.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LOUV: I would say,
start with "John Dee

00:56:17.140 --> 00:56:19.580 align:middle line:84%
